WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:41.662 --> 02:43.955
[ Electronic Beep ]

02:45.999 --> 02:48.084
[ Beeping ]

02:59.054 --> 03:00.972
[ Thud ]

04:17.507 --> 04:19.966
[ Respirator Hissing ]

05:00.717 --> 05:05.262
[ Man ]
Bio readouts are all in the green.
Looks like she's alive.

05:07.766 --> 05:10.768
Well, there goes
our salvage, guys.

05:37.212 --> 05:40.339
How are we today?
Ohh. Terrible.

05:40.424 --> 05:43.300
Well, better than
yesterday, at least.

05:43.385 --> 05:46.137
Where am I?
You're safe.

05:46.221 --> 05:48.639
You're at Gateway Station.
Been here a couple of days.

05:48.724 --> 05:52.143
You were pretty groggy at first,
but now you're okay.

05:52.227 --> 05:54.729
Oh, looks like
you've got a visitor.

05:56.606 --> 05:58.941
Jonesy. Come here.

06:00.110 --> 06:02.236
Hey, come here.

06:02.320 --> 06:04.697
How are you,
you stupid cat?

06:04.781 --> 06:08.701
How are you?
Where have you been?

06:08.785 --> 06:12.621
Guess you two
have met, huh?
I'm Burke. Carter Burke.

06:12.706 --> 06:17.251
I work for the company,
but don't let that fool you.
I'm really an okay guy.

06:18.545 --> 06:20.463
I'm glad to see you're
feeling a little better.

06:20.547 --> 06:24.091
They tell me that all
the weakness and disorientation
should pass soon.

06:24.217 --> 06:30.097
That's just natural side effects
of such an unusually long hypersleep,
or something like that.

06:30.182 --> 06:32.349
What do you mean?

06:32.434 --> 06:34.810
How long
was I out there?

06:34.895 --> 06:36.979
[ Woman On P.A. ]
Inhalation Therapy, report to-

06:37.064 --> 06:39.315
Has no one discussed
this with you yet?

06:39.399 --> 06:41.400
No.
But, I mean...

06:41.485 --> 06:45.488
I don't... recognize
this place.

06:45.572 --> 06:47.573
No, I know. Uh-

06:47.657 --> 06:51.368
Okay. It's just that,
uh, this might be
a shock to you.

06:51.495 --> 06:54.080
It's long-
How long?

06:54.164 --> 06:56.165
Please.

06:57.167 --> 07:01.128
57 years.
What?

07:01.213 --> 07:05.466
That's the thing.
You were out there
for 57 years.

07:05.550 --> 07:08.677
What happened was
you had drifted
right through the core systems.

07:08.762 --> 07:11.597
And it's really
just blind luck...

07:11.681 --> 07:14.892
that a deep-salvage team
found you when they did.

07:14.976 --> 07:17.269
It's one in a thousand,
really.

07:17.354 --> 07:22.066
I think you're damn lucky
to be alive, kiddo. You could
be floating out there forever.

07:22.150 --> 07:25.361
[ Stammering ]
You- You okay?

07:25.445 --> 07:28.280
- [ Hisses ]
- Uhh-

07:28.365 --> 07:31.700
[ Heart Pounding ]

07:31.785 --> 07:34.537
- [ Hisses ]
- Uuh!

07:34.621 --> 07:36.872
You okay?

07:36.957 --> 07:39.125
[ Groaning ]

07:41.419 --> 07:46.215
- [ Hisses ]
- Oh-h-h! Oh, God!

07:47.634 --> 07:51.178
Nurse! Please!
God!

07:51.304 --> 07:54.265
Someone get in here now!
[ Screaming ]

07:54.349 --> 07:56.392
Now!

07:56.476 --> 07:58.686
- Hold!
- Please.

07:58.770 --> 08:00.980
Hold on!

08:01.064 --> 08:03.065
Kill me!

08:10.740 --> 08:14.660
No!

08:15.662 --> 08:17.746
[ Gasping ]
Uh!

08:20.458 --> 08:23.586
Bad dreams again?
You want something
to help you sleep?

08:23.670 --> 08:25.921
No.

08:26.006 --> 08:28.007
[ Sighs ]
I've slept enough.

08:29.926 --> 08:32.177
Jonesy.

08:32.261 --> 08:34.263
Come here.

08:34.347 --> 08:36.432
[ Meows ]
Shh.

08:40.729 --> 08:42.730
It's all right.

08:43.732 --> 08:47.526
It's all right now.
[ Purring ]

08:47.611 --> 08:49.653
It's over.

08:51.448 --> 08:53.782
[ Birds Chirping ]

09:07.714 --> 09:08.797
[ Chirping Stops ]

09:08.882 --> 09:14.845
[ Woman On P.A. ]
Dr Hirsch, 334. Dr. Hirsch, 334.

09:14.930 --> 09:17.389
Hi. Sorry I'm late.
I've been running behind
all morning.

09:17.474 --> 09:20.267
Is there any word
about my daughter?

09:20.352 --> 09:23.771
Uh... I really think
we should worry
about the hearing now.

09:23.855 --> 09:27.232
'Cause we don't have a lot of time, okay?
I read your deposition, and it's great.

09:27.317 --> 09:30.361
If you just stick to that,
I think we'll be fine.
The thing to remember is,

09:30.445 --> 09:32.404
there're gonna be a lot
of heavyweights in there.

09:32.489 --> 09:34.490
You've got feds
and Interstellar
Commerce Commission,

09:34.574 --> 09:37.660
Colonial Administration,
insurance company guys-

09:37.744 --> 09:40.329
Do you have any news
about my daughter?

09:41.831 --> 09:46.001
Well, we did come up
with some information.
Why don't we sit down?

09:46.086 --> 09:49.171
I was hoping to wait
until after the inquest.

09:49.255 --> 09:51.256
Um-

09:53.259 --> 09:57.262
"Amanda Ripley-McClaren"-
married name, I guess-

09:57.347 --> 09:59.515
"Age 66."

09:59.599 --> 10:01.934
And that was at
the time of her death,

10:03.645 --> 10:06.313
which was two years ago.

10:07.565 --> 10:09.650
I'm real sorry.

10:18.785 --> 10:20.703
Amy.

10:23.915 --> 10:28.544
She was cremated and interred
at Westlake Repository,
Little Chute, Wisconsin.

10:28.628 --> 10:32.006
No children. I checked.
[ Briefcase Closes ]

10:33.633 --> 10:36.093
[ Inhales Sharply ]

10:36.177 --> 10:41.348
I promised her...
that I'd be home
for her birthday.

10:44.269 --> 10:47.229
Her 11th birthday.
[ Choking Up ]

10:50.108 --> 10:52.026
[ Sobbing ]

10:52.110 --> 10:54.361
[ Man #1 ]
I'djust like to go, uh-

10:54.446 --> 10:56.613
back to this point about
the override destruct order.

10:56.740 --> 11:00.325
[ Man #2 ]
Is it in the file?
I don't understand this.

11:00.410 --> 11:02.703
We have been here
for three and a half hours.

11:02.787 --> 11:05.080
Now, how many different ways
do you want me to tell
the same story?

11:06.499 --> 11:11.128
Look at it from
our perspective,
please.

11:11.212 --> 11:13.213
Please?

11:15.633 --> 11:18.093
Now, you freely admit to
detonating the engines of,

11:18.178 --> 11:21.013
and thereby destroying,
an M-class starsreighter,

11:21.097 --> 11:23.557
a rather expensive piece
of hardware.

11:23.641 --> 11:26.852
Forty-two million
in adjusted dollars.

11:26.936 --> 11:29.688
That's minus payload,
of course.

11:29.773 --> 11:34.151
The lifeboat's flight recorder
corroborates some elements
of your account,

11:34.235 --> 11:39.281
in that, for reasons unknown,
the Nostromo set down
on LV-426,

11:39.365 --> 11:43.911
an unsurveyed planet at that time,
that it resumed its course...

11:43.995 --> 11:48.916
and was subsequently
set for self-destruct
by you for reasons unknown.

11:49.000 --> 11:51.335
Not for reasons unknown.
I told you.

11:51.461 --> 11:57.174
We set down there
on company orders to get this thing,
which destroyed my crew...

11:57.258 --> 11:59.718
and your expensive ship.

11:59.803 --> 12:03.472
The analysis team,
which went over the lifeboat
centimeter by centimeter,

12:03.556 --> 12:06.683
found no physical evidence
of the creature you describe.

12:06.768 --> 12:10.813
Good!
That's because I blew it
out of the goddamn air lock,

12:12.482 --> 12:14.566
like I said.

12:16.319 --> 12:20.906
Are there any species
like this hostile organism
on LV-426?

12:20.990 --> 12:23.492
No. It's a rock.
No indigenous life.

12:25.495 --> 12:29.081
Did I.Q.'s just drop sharply
while I was away?

12:29.165 --> 12:31.542
Ma'am, I already said
it was not indigenous.

12:31.626 --> 12:34.378
It was a derelict spacecraft.
It was an alien ship.

12:34.462 --> 12:39.049
It was not from there.
Do you get it?
We homed in on its beacon.

12:39.134 --> 12:41.927
And found something
never recorded once...

12:42.011 --> 12:45.514
in over 300 surveyed worlds.

12:45.598 --> 12:50.394
- "A creature that gestates
inside a living human host."
- Yes.

12:50.478 --> 12:54.398
These are your words.
"And has concentrated acid
for blood."

12:54.482 --> 12:56.733
That's right.

12:56.818 --> 13:00.737
Look. I can see
where this is going,

13:00.822 --> 13:03.240
but I'm telling you
that those things exist.

13:03.366 --> 13:06.535
- Thank you, Officer Ripley.
That will be all.
- Please. You're not listening to me.

13:06.619 --> 13:09.121
Kane, the crew member-

13:09.205 --> 13:12.916
Kane, who went into that ship,
said he saw
thousands of eggs there.

13:13.042 --> 13:15.085
Thousands.
Thank you.
That will be all.

13:15.170 --> 13:17.212
Goddamn it,
that's not all!

13:17.297 --> 13:21.008
Because if one of those things
gets down here,
then that will be all!

13:21.092 --> 13:23.635
Then all of this-
this bullshit that you think
is so important-

13:23.720 --> 13:27.514
You can just kiss
all of that good-bye!

13:33.271 --> 13:35.606
It is the finding
of this court of inquiry that...

13:35.690 --> 13:37.774
Warrant Officer E. Ripley,

13:37.859 --> 13:40.903
NOC14472,

13:40.987 --> 13:43.739
has acted with
questionable judgment...

13:43.823 --> 13:48.243
and is unfit to hold
an I.C.C. license
as a commercial flight officer.

13:49.996 --> 13:53.415
Said license is hereby
suspended indefinitely.

13:55.251 --> 13:59.588
Now, no criminal charges
will be filed against you
at this time,

13:59.672 --> 14:01.924
and you are released
on your own recognizance...

14:02.008 --> 14:04.801
for a six-month period
ofpsychometric probation,

14:04.886 --> 14:10.390
to include monthly review
by an I.C.C. psychiatric technician.

14:12.185 --> 14:15.062
These proceedings are closed.

14:26.032 --> 14:28.158
That could have
been better.

14:28.284 --> 14:31.703
Look, I think the-
Ripley?
Van Leuwen.

14:31.788 --> 14:35.040
Why don't you
just check out LV-426?

14:35.124 --> 14:38.877
Because I don't have to.
There have been people there
for over 20 years,

14:39.003 --> 14:43.674
and they never complained
about any hostile organism.
What do you mean? What people?

14:43.758 --> 14:46.885
Terraformers.
Planet engineers.

14:46.970 --> 14:50.722
They go in, set up these
big atmosphere processors
to make the air breathable.

14:50.807 --> 14:53.058
Takes decades.

14:53.142 --> 14:55.394
It's what we call
a "Shake 'N Bake" colony.

14:55.478 --> 14:59.106
How many are there?
How many colonists?

14:59.190 --> 15:03.694
I don't know-
60, maybe 70 families.
Do you mind?

15:06.364 --> 15:08.365
Families.

15:10.618 --> 15:12.619
Jesus.

15:13.621 --> 15:15.664
[ Wind Howling ]

15:37.186 --> 15:39.271
[ Horn Honking ]

16:13.973 --> 16:16.058
[ Low Chattering ]

16:18.519 --> 16:20.687
[ Woman On P.A.,
Indistinct ]

16:24.359 --> 16:27.778
[ Machines Clacking ]

16:27.862 --> 16:30.322
I'll be down
in maintenance, okay?
Al!

16:30.406 --> 16:32.324
What?
Hey, Al.

16:32.450 --> 16:34.618
What?
Remember you sent
some wildcatters...

16:34.702 --> 16:37.537
out to the middle
of nowhere last week,
out past the Ilium Range?

16:37.622 --> 16:41.500
- Yeah, what?
- One of them's on the horn,
a mom-and-pop survey team.

16:41.584 --> 16:44.336
He says he's onto something.
He wants to know if
his claim will be honored.

16:44.420 --> 16:46.463
Why wouldn't his claim
be honored?

16:46.589 --> 16:49.633
Well, because you sent them to that
particular middle-of-nowhere
on company orders, maybe.

16:49.759 --> 16:53.261
I don't know.
Christ! Some honch in
a cushy office on Earth...

16:53.346 --> 16:55.472
says, "Go look at
a grid reference."

16:55.556 --> 16:58.767
We look.
They don't say why,
and I don't ask.

16:58.893 --> 17:02.979
I don't ask, because it takes
two weeks to get an answer out here,
and the answer is always-

17:03.064 --> 17:04.940
[ Together ]
"Don't ask."

17:05.066 --> 17:07.192
So what do l
tell this guy?
[ Sighs ]

17:07.276 --> 17:10.487
Tell him as far as
I'm concerned, if he
finds something, it is his.

17:10.613 --> 17:12.489
Lydecker?
What?

17:12.615 --> 17:15.157
[ Giggling ]
You kids know you're not
supposed to be on this level!

17:15.284 --> 17:17.618
Go on!
Get outta here!
[ Giggling ]

17:49.068 --> 17:54.406
[ Boy ] Do too. You go
in places we can't fit.
So? That's why I'm the best.

17:54.490 --> 17:59.161
Knock it off! I catch either
of you playing in the air ducts
again, l'll tan your hides.

17:59.245 --> 18:01.496
Mom, all the kids play-

18:01.581 --> 18:04.166
Wait a minute.
Annie, come and have
a look at this, will ya?

18:14.886 --> 18:17.846
Folks, we have
scored big this time.

18:23.936 --> 18:26.813
What is it, Dad?

18:30.401 --> 18:33.361
I'm not sure.

18:33.488 --> 18:37.282
Let's see if we can't get a
closer look at this thing, maybe
through that crack there on the side.

18:37.366 --> 18:41.495
- Shouldn't we call in?
- Let's wait till we know
what to call it in as.

18:44.123 --> 18:47.584
[ Brakes Hiss ]
[ Dad ] That's about as close
as we can get.

18:47.668 --> 18:50.754
Should we take
a look inside?

18:54.133 --> 18:56.384
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

19:01.140 --> 19:03.183
[ Wind Whistling ]

19:06.354 --> 19:09.606
You two stay inside.
I mean it.
We'll be right back.

19:09.690 --> 19:11.733
Okay.
Bye.

19:26.123 --> 19:28.083
[ Thunderclap ]

20:20.678 --> 20:24.139
[ Radio Chatter, Indistinct ]

20:27.560 --> 20:29.477
Huh?

20:29.562 --> 20:32.689
Timmy, they've been gone
a long time.

20:32.773 --> 20:35.150
It'll be okay, Newt.
Dad knows what he's doing.

20:35.276 --> 20:41.072
[ Banging ]
Mayday, Mayday! This is Alpha Kilo
Two Four Niner calling!

20:41.157 --> 20:44.117
This is Alpha Kilo
Two Four Niner!

20:44.243 --> 20:46.536
[ Screaming ]
Alpha Kilo
Two Four Niner calling!

21:15.941 --> 21:17.317
[ Meowing ]

21:23.824 --> 21:25.867
[ Doorbell Beeps ]

21:27.036 --> 21:30.121
[ Clears Throat ]

21:30.206 --> 21:32.415
Hiya, Ripley.
This is Lieutenant Gorman...

21:32.500 --> 21:35.627
of the Colonial
Marine Corps-

21:35.711 --> 21:37.962
Ripley,
we have to talk.

21:38.047 --> 21:41.758
We've lost contact
with the colony on LV-426.

21:48.224 --> 21:50.433
I don't believe this.

21:50.559 --> 21:55.105
You guys throw me at the wolves,
and now you want me
to go back out there?

21:55.189 --> 21:57.774
Forget it.
It's not my problem.

21:57.900 --> 22:01.486
Can I finish?
No.
There's no way.

22:02.905 --> 22:04.989
Ripley, you wouldn't
be going in
with the troops.

22:05.074 --> 22:07.409
I can guarantee
your safety.

22:07.493 --> 22:09.994
These Colonial Marines
are very tough hombres.

22:10.079 --> 22:12.956
They're packing
state-of-the-art
firepower.

22:13.040 --> 22:14.207
There's nothing
they can't handle.

22:15.584 --> 22:17.919
- Lieutenant, am I right?
- That's true.

22:18.003 --> 22:20.171
We've been trained
to deal with situations
like this.

22:20.256 --> 22:23.925
Then you don't need me.
I'm not a soldier.

22:24.009 --> 22:26.594
[ Burke ]
Yeah, but we don't know exactly
what's going on out there.

22:26.679 --> 22:29.305
It mayjust be
a downed transmitter,
okay?

22:29.390 --> 22:33.852
But if it's not,
I would like you there
as an adviser,

22:33.936 --> 22:35.979
and that's all.

22:37.982 --> 22:40.817
What's your interest
in all this?
Why are you going?

22:40.901 --> 22:43.945
Corporation cofinanced
that colony,

22:44.029 --> 22:46.531
along with
Colonial Administration.

22:46.615 --> 22:49.451
We're getting into a lot
of terraforming now.
"Building Better Worlds"-

22:49.535 --> 22:52.036
Yeah, yeah.
I saw the commercial.

22:52.121 --> 22:55.039
Look, I don't have time
for this. I've got
to get to work.

22:55.124 --> 22:58.251
Oh, right. I heard you're
working the cargo docks.

22:58.335 --> 23:00.336
That's right.

23:00.463 --> 23:03.131
Running loaders and forklifts,
that sort of thing?
Yeah. So?

23:03.215 --> 23:06.384
Nothing. I think it's great
that you're keeping busy.

23:06.469 --> 23:08.970
And I know it's the only
thing that you could get.

23:09.054 --> 23:10.889
There's nothing wrong
with it.

23:14.143 --> 23:16.603
What would you say
if I told you I could
get you reinstated...

23:16.687 --> 23:18.646
as a flight officer?

23:18.772 --> 23:23.234
The company's already agreed
to pick up your contract.
If I go.

23:23.319 --> 23:26.279
Yeah, if you go.

23:26.363 --> 23:28.531
Come on.
That's a second chance, kiddo.

23:28.616 --> 23:31.367
I think, personally,
for you, it would be
the best thing in the world...

23:31.452 --> 23:34.329
to get out there
and face this thing,
get back on the horse.

23:34.413 --> 23:37.332
Spare me, Burke.
I've had my psych evaluation
this month.

23:37.458 --> 23:41.544
Yeah, I know. I've read it. You wake
up every night. Your sheets
are soaking with sweat-

23:41.629 --> 23:43.880
I said no,
and I mean it!

23:46.675 --> 23:49.552
Now, please leave.
I am not going back.

23:49.637 --> 23:52.972
And I am- I would not be
any good to you if I did.

23:53.057 --> 23:56.142
Okay. Shh.

23:57.561 --> 24:01.064
Would you
do me a favor?
Just think about it.

24:04.151 --> 24:06.194
Thanks
for the coffee.

24:10.241 --> 24:13.284
[ Door Opens, Closes ]

24:15.037 --> 24:17.038
[ Meows ]

24:18.290 --> 24:21.292
[ Screaming, Panting ]

24:25.714 --> 24:27.715
Oh!

24:29.385 --> 24:31.386
[ Sobbing ]

24:45.651 --> 24:47.735
[ Water Running ]

25:04.336 --> 25:06.254
[ Beeping ]

25:14.263 --> 25:16.180
Hello.

25:16.265 --> 25:18.975
Ripley.

25:19.101 --> 25:22.645
You okay?
Just tell me
one thing, Burke.

25:22.730 --> 25:26.024
You're going out there
to destroy them, right?

25:26.108 --> 25:31.029
Not to study, not to bring back,
but to wipe them out.

25:31.113 --> 25:35.158
That's the plan.
You have my word on it.

25:37.703 --> 25:38.911
All right. I'm in.

25:40.289 --> 25:40.955
I think that-

25:49.131 --> 25:51.424
And you,
you little shithead,

25:51.508 --> 25:54.344
[ Chuckles ]
you're staying here.

26:20.329 --> 26:22.330
[ Creaking ]

27:41.076 --> 27:43.453
[ Beeping ]

27:50.502 --> 27:52.503
[ Whirring ]

28:09.229 --> 28:11.230
Mmm.

28:16.570 --> 28:18.529
[ Coughing ]

28:20.741 --> 28:23.451
[ Groans ]

28:26.538 --> 28:30.374
They ain't payin' us
enough for this, man.

28:30.459 --> 28:32.877
Not enough
to have to wake up
to your face, Drake.

28:32.961 --> 28:33.461
What?

28:34.838 --> 28:36.088
Is that a joke?

28:36.173 --> 28:38.257
Oh, I wish it were.

28:38.342 --> 28:43.262
Hey, Hicks. Man, you look
just like I feel.
[ Grunts ]

28:43.347 --> 28:47.225
- [ Coughing ]
- All right, sweethearts.
What are you waiting for?

28:47.309 --> 28:50.436
Breakfast in bed?
Another glorious day
in the corps.

28:50.521 --> 28:54.023
A day in the Marine Corps
is like a day on the farm-

28:54.107 --> 28:59.070
every meal's a banquet,
every paycheck a fortune,
every formation a parade.

28:59.196 --> 29:00.863
I love the corps!
Christ!

29:00.948 --> 29:02.782
Man, this floor is freezing!

29:02.908 --> 29:07.078
What do you want me to do?
Fetch your slippers for ya?
Gee, would you, sir? I'd like that.

29:07.162 --> 29:10.414
Look into my eye.
Fall in, people.

29:10.499 --> 29:12.750
Come on. Let's go.

29:12.834 --> 29:14.794
I hate this job.

29:14.920 --> 29:17.588
Crowe, Wierzbowski.
Come on. On your feet.
We got some slack coming, right?

29:17.673 --> 29:20.550
You had three weeks
on your back, Frost.
What do you want?

29:20.634 --> 29:23.010
[ Frost ]
I'm talking about breathing,
not this frozen shit.

29:23.095 --> 29:25.388
[ Dietrich ]
Yeah, Top. How 'bout it?

29:28.517 --> 29:32.687
[Apone ]
All right. First assembly's
in 15, people. Shag it.

29:33.939 --> 29:36.566
Hey, mira.
Who's Snow White?

29:36.650 --> 29:40.111
She's supposed to be
some kind of consultant.

29:40.195 --> 29:42.446
Apparently,
she saw an alien once.

29:42.531 --> 29:45.575
Whoopee-fuckin'-do!
Hey, I'm impressed.

29:45.659 --> 29:47.702
iQue bonita!

29:50.038 --> 29:54.166
Hey, Vasquez.
Have you ever been
mistaken for a man?

29:54.251 --> 29:56.294
No. Have you?

29:56.378 --> 30:01.215
Ha, ha!
Oh, Vasquez.
You're just too bad.

30:01.925 --> 30:03.634
Uhh!

30:03.719 --> 30:06.012
[ Chattering ]

30:12.060 --> 30:14.604
Hey, Top,
what's the op?

30:14.688 --> 30:16.814
It's a rescue mission.
You'll love it.

30:16.898 --> 30:21.611
There's some juicy
colonists' daughters we have
to rescue from their virginity.

30:21.695 --> 30:23.863
[ Spunkmeyer]
Dumb-ass colonists.

30:26.450 --> 30:30.077
What's this crap
supposed to be?
Vasquez.

30:30.203 --> 30:33.289
Corn bread, I think.
It's good for you, boy.
Eat it.

30:33.373 --> 30:36.375
Hey, sure wouldn't mind
getting some more
of that Arcturian poontang.

30:36.460 --> 30:41.589
- Remember that time?
- Yeah. Except the one
that you had was male.

30:41.673 --> 30:44.258
Doesn't matter
when it's Arcturian.

30:44.384 --> 30:46.802
Hey, Bishop, man.
Do the thing with the knife.
Oh, please.

30:46.928 --> 30:49.347
Oh, come on. Yeah.
[ All Goading ]

30:49.431 --> 30:51.390
All right! Yeah.

30:51.475 --> 30:55.061
- I don't want to see that, man.
- Come on, man.
All right. All right.

30:55.145 --> 30:58.105
Hey, what are you doing, man?
What are you doing?

30:58.231 --> 31:00.358
Come on.
Quit messing around, Drake.
Hudson, shut up !

31:00.442 --> 31:03.027
- Bishop, hey, man.
- [ Drake ] Do it, Bishop!

31:03.111 --> 31:06.697
Hey! Not me, man!
Quit messing around!
Yeah, you! Don't move.

31:06.782 --> 31:09.075
Trust me.

31:10.369 --> 31:12.286
Aah!

31:20.796 --> 31:23.756
[Apone ]
All right. Knock it off,
knock it off.

31:23.840 --> 31:25.841
- Thank you.
- [ Drake Chuckles ]

31:28.303 --> 31:30.304
There you go,
short shit.
Enjoy your meal.

31:30.389 --> 31:33.140
That wasn't funny, man.

31:36.687 --> 31:39.814
Lieutenant Gorman?
Mr. Burke?
Yeah, thanks.

31:39.898 --> 31:45.069
Looks like the new lieutenant's
too good to eat with
the rest of us grunts.

31:46.488 --> 31:49.657
Boy's definitely got
a corncob up his ass.

31:50.742 --> 31:53.452
[ Burke ]
Thought you
never miss, Bishop.

31:56.748 --> 31:59.542
You never said anything about
an android being on board.
Why not?

31:59.626 --> 32:03.671
[ Chuckles ]
It never-
never occurred to me.

32:03.755 --> 32:06.841
It's just common practice.
We always have
a synthetic on board.

32:06.925 --> 32:09.385
I prefer the term
"artificial person" myself.

32:09.469 --> 32:11.345
Right.

32:11.430 --> 32:14.098
- Is there a problem?
- [ Burke ] I'm sorry.

32:14.182 --> 32:16.100
I don't know why
I didn't even-

32:16.184 --> 32:19.603
Ripley's last trip out,
the syn- the artificial person
malfunctioned.

32:19.688 --> 32:24.567
- Malfunctioned?
- There were problems and
a few deaths were involved.

32:24.651 --> 32:27.862
I'm shocked.
Was it an older model?

32:27.946 --> 32:30.614
The Hyperdyne Systems
1 20-A2.

32:30.699 --> 32:33.284
That explains it then.
The A2s always were
a bit twitchy.

32:33.368 --> 32:36.078
That could never happen now
with our behavioral inhibitors.

32:36.163 --> 32:40.750
It is impossible for me to harm,
or by omission ofaction, allow
to be harmed, a human being.

32:40.834 --> 32:45.045
- You sure you
don't want some?
- [ Clattering ]

32:45.130 --> 32:47.715
You just stay away from me,
Bishop. You got that straight?

32:50.510 --> 32:53.846
Guess she don't like
the corn bread, either.

32:57.768 --> 33:00.853
[ Chattering ]

33:07.194 --> 33:11.322
[ Apone ] Squad, ten-hut!
Officer on deck!
As you were.

33:11.406 --> 33:14.241
Quickly, quickly.
Settle down.

33:14.326 --> 33:17.328
All right.
Listen up!

33:17.412 --> 33:22.458
Morning, marines. l'm sorry we
didn't have time to brief you
people before we left Gateway-

33:22.584 --> 33:25.044
[ Hudson ]
Sir?
What is it, Hicks?

33:25.128 --> 33:28.214
Hudson, sir.
He's Hicks.

33:28.298 --> 33:31.217
What's the question?

33:31.301 --> 33:35.095
Is this gonna be
a stand-up fight, sir,
or another bug hunt?

33:35.180 --> 33:39.266
All we know is that
there's still no contact
with the colony...

33:39.351 --> 33:42.186
and that a xenomorph
may be involved.

33:42.312 --> 33:45.022
Excuse me, sir.
A what?
A xenomorph.

33:45.106 --> 33:47.358
It's a bug hunt.

33:47.442 --> 33:52.154
- What exactly are
we dealing with here?
- Ripley.

33:52.239 --> 33:54.657
I'll tell you
what I know.

33:54.741 --> 33:57.159
We set down
on LV-426.

33:57.244 --> 34:01.247
One ofour crew members was
brought back on board with
something attached to his face,

34:01.331 --> 34:03.833
some kind of parasite.

34:03.917 --> 34:06.252
We tried to get it off.
It wouldn't come off.

34:06.336 --> 34:09.255
Later, it seemed to come off
by itselfand die.

34:09.339 --> 34:11.882
Kane seemed fine.

34:11.967 --> 34:14.092
We were all having dinner,
and, um,

34:14.177 --> 34:18.304
it must have laid something
inside his throat,
some sort of embryo.

34:18.431 --> 34:22.393
He started- Um, he-
[ Vasquez ]
Look, man.

34:22.476 --> 34:27.523
I only need
to know one thing-
where they are.

34:27.649 --> 34:30.400
Yo, Vasquez.
Kick ass.
Anytime, anywhere.

34:30.485 --> 34:35.322
Right, right. Somebody said
"alien." She thought they said
"illegal alien" and signed up.

34:35.447 --> 34:37.408
Fuck you, man.
Anytime,
anywhere.

34:37.492 --> 34:40.119
Are you finished?

34:45.292 --> 34:48.002
I hope you're right.
I really do.

34:50.255 --> 34:53.299
Yeah, okay, right.
Thank you, Ripley.

34:53.382 --> 34:56.302
We also have Ripley's
report on disk.
I suggest you study it.

34:56.428 --> 35:01.307
Because just one of those things
managed to wipe out my entire crew
in less than 24 hours.

35:01.391 --> 35:04.143
And if the colonists
have found that ship,
then there's no telling...

35:04.227 --> 35:05.895
how many of them
have been exposed.

35:05.979 --> 35:08.397
Do you understand?

35:10.150 --> 35:13.402
Anyway, we have it on disk,
so you better look at it.

35:13.486 --> 35:16.155
Any questions?

35:16.239 --> 35:18.616
What is it, Private?

35:18.700 --> 35:21.702
How do I get out of this
chickenshit outfit?

35:21.786 --> 35:23.537
You secure that shit,
Hudson.

35:26.207 --> 35:28.292
All right.

35:28.376 --> 35:31.211
Now listen up.

35:32.589 --> 35:34.715
I want this thing
to go smooth...

35:34.799 --> 35:37.343
and by the numbers.

35:37.427 --> 35:41.847
I want D.C.S.
and tactical database
assimilation by 0830.

35:41.973 --> 35:44.934
[ All Scoffing ]
Ordinance loading, weapons strip
and drop-ship prep details...

35:45.060 --> 35:47.436
will have
seven hours.
Oh, come on.

35:47.520 --> 35:49.688
Now, move it,
people!

35:49.773 --> 35:52.483
All right, sweethearts.
You heard the man,
and you know the drill.

35:52.567 --> 35:56.779
Assholes and elbows!
Hudson, come here.
Come here.

36:12.003 --> 36:14.004
I don't care if you
are short, Hudson.
Get it done.

36:14.089 --> 36:16.674
Hey, Sarge.
You'll get lip cancer
smoking those.

36:16.758 --> 36:19.885
Corporal, I want this
loading lock sealed.
Now!

36:20.011 --> 36:22.429
How many more you got,
Spunkmeyer?
Last one.

36:22.514 --> 36:24.556
Good. Take it away.

36:24.641 --> 36:26.809
[ Whirring, Thudding ]

36:41.992 --> 36:44.076
Clear behind.

36:50.250 --> 36:52.876
Did you check number three?
Let me see that.

36:52.961 --> 36:56.880
Hi. I feel like kind of
a fifth wheel around here.
Is there anything I can do?

36:56.965 --> 36:59.341
I don't know.
Is there anything
you can do?

37:02.303 --> 37:04.555
Well, I can drive
that loader.

37:04.639 --> 37:08.308
I have a Class 2 rating.

37:08.393 --> 37:10.477
Be my guest.

37:26.036 --> 37:28.454
[ Whirring ]

37:56.024 --> 37:59.943
- Where you want it?
- [ Chuckles ]

38:00.028 --> 38:03.489
[ Laughing ]
Bay 12, please.

38:29.933 --> 38:32.351
[ Engines Revving ]

38:59.838 --> 39:03.298
[Apone ] All right,
sweethearts. We're a team, and
there's nothing to worry about.

39:03.383 --> 39:06.885
We come here,
and we gonna conquer,
and we gonna kick some.

39:07.011 --> 39:09.888
Is that understood? That's what
we gonna do, sweethearts.
Yes, sir.

39:09.973 --> 39:12.307
We are going to go
and get some.
Hey.

39:12.392 --> 39:15.144
All right, people!
On the ready line!

39:15.270 --> 39:18.021
Are you lean?
Are you mean?
[All ] Yeah! Yeah!

39:18.148 --> 39:20.774
What are you?
What are you?
Lean and mean!

39:20.859 --> 39:23.652
Hudson!
Get on the ready line,
marine!

39:23.736 --> 39:26.655
Get some today!
Get on the ready line!

39:26.781 --> 39:29.700
Yo!
Move it out!
Move it out, goddamn it!

39:29.784 --> 39:33.370
Get hot! One, two, three!
Get out, get out, get out!

39:33.454 --> 39:36.999
Move it out, move it out,
move it out! Move it out,
move it out, move it out!

39:37.083 --> 39:39.668
[ Barking Orders,
Indistinct ]

39:39.752 --> 39:43.380
[ Growls ]
Absolutely badasses.

39:43.464 --> 39:45.883
Let's pack 'em in.
Get in there!

39:45.967 --> 39:47.926
All right! Move it!

39:48.052 --> 39:50.721
Let's go, let's go!
One, two, three,

39:50.805 --> 39:54.266
four, five, six!

39:54.350 --> 39:58.729
All right.
I want combat seating.
You know your places.

39:58.813 --> 40:01.106
Get those weapons stowed.
Let's go.

40:01.191 --> 40:04.526
Come on.
Settle down, people.

40:04.611 --> 40:06.695
Lock 'em in, Hudson.

40:06.821 --> 40:10.199
Ready to get it on?
You know it!

40:10.283 --> 40:12.951
Okay, Bishop,
let's go.

40:13.036 --> 40:15.204
Roger.

40:16.998 --> 40:19.708
I'm ready, man.

40:19.834 --> 40:23.337
Ready to get it on!
Go!
[ Murmurs Of Agreement ]

40:27.467 --> 40:31.470
[ Ferro On Headsets ]
Stand by. Cross-locking now.
Prelaunch autocycle engaged.

40:34.724 --> 40:38.727
Primary couplers released.
Hit the internals.

40:50.281 --> 40:52.991
Shit, man.
Confirm cross-lock
and drop stations secured.

40:53.076 --> 40:57.204
[ Gorman ]
Affirmative.
All drop stations secured.

41:00.875 --> 41:03.418
Stand by. Ten seconds.

41:06.047 --> 41:10.092
Stand by to initiate
release sequencer...
on my mark.

41:10.176 --> 41:14.846
- Five, four, three,
- We're on an express elevator
to hell, going down.

41:14.931 --> 41:17.891
two, one, mark.

41:19.060 --> 41:21.436
Woo-hoo!

41:33.700 --> 41:38.078
- Switch to D.C.S. ranging.
- [ Spunkmeyer]
240, nominal to profile.

41:38.162 --> 41:40.872
We're in the pipe,
five by five.

41:51.592 --> 41:53.760
We're picking up
some hull ionization.

41:53.845 --> 41:56.305
Got it.
Rough air ahead.

41:56.389 --> 41:58.640
We're in for some chop.
[ Rumbling ]

42:12.280 --> 42:14.614
How many drops is this
for you, Lieutenant?

42:16.951 --> 42:19.369
Thirty-eight.

42:19.454 --> 42:21.413
Simulated.

42:21.497 --> 42:23.623
How many combat drops?

42:23.708 --> 42:27.753
Uh, two...
including this one.

42:27.837 --> 42:31.173
- Shit.
- Oh, man!

42:43.853 --> 42:48.065
Range 014.
Turning on final.

42:52.945 --> 42:55.822
[ Frost ] And I'm telling you,
I got a bad feeling
about this drop.

42:55.907 --> 42:59.326
[ Crowe ] You always say that,
Frost. You always say, "I got
a bad feeling about this drop."

42:59.410 --> 43:01.828
[ Frost ]
Okay, okay.
When we get back without you,

43:01.954 --> 43:04.956
I'll call your folks.
[ Laughs ]
[ Beeping ]

43:07.210 --> 43:11.338
All right.
Let's see what we can see.

43:11.422 --> 43:14.883
Everybody online.
Looking good.

43:16.719 --> 43:19.012
Drake, check your camera.
There seems to be
a malfunction.

43:20.390 --> 43:23.683
That's better.
Pan it around a bit.

43:23.768 --> 43:26.853
- Good.
- I'm ready, man. Check it out.

43:26.979 --> 43:30.023
I am the ultimate badass.
Yeah.
That's right.

43:30.149 --> 43:35.570
State-of-the-badass art.
You do not want to fuck with me.
Who here's runnin'?

43:35.655 --> 43:38.532
Check it out.
[ Chuckles ]

43:39.742 --> 43:42.494
Hey, Ripley,
don't worry.

43:42.578 --> 43:45.705
Me and my squad of
ultimate badasses
will protect you.

43:45.790 --> 43:47.707
Hey!
That's right.

43:47.792 --> 43:49.960
Check it out.

43:50.044 --> 43:53.588
Independently targeting
particle-beam phalanx.

43:53.673 --> 43:57.300
[ Imitates Blast Noise ]
Fry halfa city
with this puppy.

43:57.385 --> 43:59.761
We got tactical
smart missiles,

43:59.846 --> 44:02.264
phase-plasma pulse rifles,
R.P.G.'s.

44:02.348 --> 44:05.809
- We got sonic,
electronic ball breakers!
- [ Vasquez ] Whoo!

44:05.893 --> 44:09.229
We got nukes, we got knives,
sharp sticks-

44:09.313 --> 44:12.232
Knock it off, Hudson.
All right, gear up.

44:12.316 --> 44:16.111
Two minutes, people.
Get hot.

44:16.195 --> 44:17.904
Somebody wake up Hicks.

44:31.419 --> 44:33.837
Coming around
for a 709er.

44:33.963 --> 44:36.840
Terminal guidance
locked in.
Where's the damn beacon?

44:36.924 --> 44:39.426
Oh, I see it.

44:45.600 --> 44:48.894
That's the atmosphere
processor?
Yep, that's it.

44:48.978 --> 44:52.272
Remarkable piece
of machinery.
Completely automated.

44:52.356 --> 44:54.900
You know,
we manufacture those,
by the way.

45:04.535 --> 45:09.748
[ Gorman ] Okay, Ferro.
Take us in low over
the main colony complex.

45:11.459 --> 45:13.543
Storm shutters are sealed.

45:13.628 --> 45:16.213
There's no visible activity.
All right. Hold at 40.

45:17.632 --> 45:20.467
[ Ferro On Headset ] Roger.
Give me a slow circle
of the complex.

45:28.351 --> 45:32.687
Structure seems intact.
They still have power.

45:32.772 --> 45:36.983
Okay, Ferro.
Set down on
the landing grid.

45:37.068 --> 45:39.986
Immediate dust off
on my clear,
then stay on station.

45:54.001 --> 45:56.336
[ Ferro ]
Down and clear.

45:57.505 --> 45:59.673
Ten seconds, people.
Look sharp.

46:02.718 --> 46:06.054
All right. I want a nice,
clean dispersal this time.

46:07.723 --> 46:09.808
Let's go!
Move it out!

46:09.892 --> 46:11.893
Head 'em up!

46:32.790 --> 46:37.002
First squad up on line.
Hicks, get yours in accord
and watch the rear.

46:37.086 --> 46:40.714
Vasquez, take point.
Let's move!

46:48.097 --> 46:50.056
Move up.

46:51.934 --> 46:55.020
Hudson, run a bypass.

47:00.443 --> 47:03.361
Second squad, move up.
Flanking positions.

47:03.446 --> 47:06.156
[ Apone Over Headsets ]
Second squad on line.

47:12.455 --> 47:13.622
[ Door Lock Clicks ]

47:34.185 --> 47:36.269
[ Whispers ]
You set?

47:39.315 --> 47:41.316
Go on.

48:06.759 --> 48:09.678
Second team, move inside.
Hicks, take the upper level.

48:37.707 --> 48:42.711
[ Apone ]
Sir, you copying this? Looks
like hits from small-arms fire.

48:42.795 --> 48:45.880
Uh, we got some
explosives damage.

48:45.965 --> 48:48.216
It's probably seismic
survey charges.

48:48.300 --> 48:52.095
Are you reading this?
Keep it tight, people.

49:05.359 --> 49:09.320
[ Gorman ]
All right. Hicks, Hudson,
use your motion trackers.

49:11.699 --> 49:14.200
[ Clicking ]

49:27.131 --> 49:30.467
Nothing.
Not a goddamn thing.

49:35.389 --> 49:38.224
Quarter and search
by twos.

49:41.687 --> 49:43.688
[ Snaps Fingers ]

49:49.653 --> 49:52.614
Okay. Dietrich,
Frost, you're up.

49:59.246 --> 50:01.247
[ Sniffs ]

50:04.835 --> 50:06.711
[ Clicking Continues ]

50:21.602 --> 50:23.895
[ Beeping ]

50:39.787 --> 50:41.621
It's right in there.

50:45.626 --> 50:49.629
[ High-pitched Beeping ]

50:54.009 --> 50:54.842
Now!
Now!

50:54.927 --> 50:59.722
- Haah! Uh-
- Good one, Hudson!

50:59.807 --> 51:04.936
[ Hudson ] Uh, sir, uh, we have
a negative situation here.
Uh, movin' on, sir

51:05.020 --> 51:07.564
[ Clicking ]

51:13.988 --> 51:16.948
Wait. Wait,
tell him to-

51:17.950 --> 51:21.661
Hicks, back up.
Pan right.

51:22.830 --> 51:28.418
- There.
- You seeing this all right?

51:28.502 --> 51:34.048
Looks melted.
Somebody must have bagged
one of Ripley's bad guys here.

51:34.133 --> 51:36.092
Acid for blood.

51:36.176 --> 51:39.762
If you like that,
you're gonna love this.

51:46.812 --> 51:48.813
[ Hocking ]

51:52.943 --> 51:54.652
Quit screwing around.

51:54.737 --> 51:56.487
Second squad,
what's your status?

51:56.572 --> 51:59.699
[ Hicks ]
Uh, we just finished our sweep.
Nobody's home.

51:59.783 --> 52:02.368
Roger.
Sir, this place is dead.

52:02.453 --> 52:05.079
Whatever happened here,
I think we missed it.

52:05.164 --> 52:09.167
[ Sighs ] All right. The area's
secured. Let's go in and see
what their computer can tell us.

52:09.251 --> 52:12.086
- Wait a minute.
It's not secure.
- The area's secured, Ripley.

52:12.171 --> 52:13.963
First team,
head for operations.

52:15.382 --> 52:18.301
Hudson, see if you can
get their C.P.U. on line.
Affirmative.

52:18.427 --> 52:21.888
Hicks, meet me at
the south lock. We're coming in.
Roger.

52:21.972 --> 52:25.266
He's comin' in.
I feel safer already.

52:25.351 --> 52:27.393
Pendejo jerk-off.

52:47.456 --> 52:51.417
[ Hudson On Radio ]
Sir, we got the C.P.U. on line.
No problem.

52:51.502 --> 52:54.212
Good. Stand by
in Operations.

52:55.214 --> 52:57.256
Okay, let's go.

53:17.611 --> 53:19.278
Are you all right?

53:20.489 --> 53:22.156
Yes.

53:38.757 --> 53:42.760
Sir, they sealed off
this wing at both ends,

53:42.845 --> 53:46.097
welded the doors
and blocked off the stairs
with heavy equipment.

53:46.181 --> 53:50.184
[ Gorman ] Mm-hmm.
But it looks like
the barricade didn't hold.

53:50.310 --> 53:52.437
Any bodies?
No, sir.

53:52.521 --> 53:54.439
Last stand.

53:54.523 --> 53:56.983
[ Drake ]
Must have been
a hell ofa fight.

53:57.067 --> 53:59.694
Yeah, looks that way.

54:01.613 --> 54:03.739
[ Gorman ]
All right, Drake, this way.

54:03.824 --> 54:06.826
We should be able
to cut through the medlab
to Operations.

54:58.629 --> 55:00.546
[ Hicks ]
Lieutenant.

55:02.382 --> 55:04.383
Gorman.

55:21.276 --> 55:22.944
Are those the same ones that-

55:36.208 --> 55:38.251
Careful, Burke.

55:47.844 --> 55:51.764
Looks like love
at first sight to me.

55:51.848 --> 55:54.183
Oh, he likes you, Burke.
[ Chuckles ]

55:54.268 --> 55:56.894
Two are alive.
The rest are dead.

55:58.772 --> 56:01.732
"Surgically removed
before embryo implantation.

56:01.817 --> 56:06.529
Subject Marachek, John J.,
died during the procedure."

56:06.613 --> 56:09.031
They killed him
taking it off.

56:09.116 --> 56:13.286
[ Clicking, Beeping ]
Yo, Hicks.

56:13.370 --> 56:15.913
I think we got
something here.

56:20.669 --> 56:22.628
Behind us.
One of us?

56:23.922 --> 56:27.425
Apone, where are your people?
Anybody in "D" block?

56:27.509 --> 56:30.344
[ Apone On Radio ]
Ah, that's a negative.
We're all in Operations.

56:33.348 --> 56:35.391
Talk to me,
Frosty.

56:35.475 --> 56:37.435
Let's keep moving, baby.

56:49.156 --> 56:50.990
[ Crash ]

56:55.871 --> 56:57.830
It's moving.
Which way?

56:57.914 --> 57:01.459
It's coming
straight for us.
Straight up.

57:20.979 --> 57:24.023
[ High-pitched Beeping ]

57:38.997 --> 57:40.956
Fuck!
Hold up.

57:42.542 --> 57:44.043
Ripley.

58:03.563 --> 58:06.649
Hey. Shh.
It's all right.

58:06.775 --> 58:09.026
It's all right.
Come on.
Just grab her, Corporal.

58:09.111 --> 58:12.196
Don't be afraid. Come on.
We won't hurt you.

58:12.280 --> 58:14.573
Shh. It's all right.
It's okay.

58:14.658 --> 58:16.826
Come on out. Come on.

58:16.910 --> 58:18.994
- Easy. Easy.
- I got her.

58:19.079 --> 58:20.996
Ow! Damn!

58:21.081 --> 58:23.833
Watch her!
She's under the grille!
Don't let her go.

58:23.959 --> 58:27.253
Frost, get your light
up here.
Where'd she go?

58:30.173 --> 58:33.968
Shine the light.
Here. Here.

58:34.094 --> 58:35.803
Here. Here.
There she is.

58:35.887 --> 58:38.472
[ Ripley ]
Keep back. Keep back.
Don't scare her.

58:38.598 --> 58:41.267
[ Hicks ] Grab her, man.
We're gonna lose her.
[ Ripley ] Damn it!

58:43.562 --> 58:45.479
[ Hicks ]
Kick it out!

58:46.523 --> 58:49.692
[ Grunts ]
Wait.

59:13.341 --> 59:15.259
[ Clattering ]

59:15.343 --> 59:18.304
It's okay.
It's all right.

59:19.306 --> 59:23.100
Don't be afraid.

59:23.185 --> 59:25.227
See?

59:25.353 --> 59:27.271
Wait.
No, you don't.
[ Screams ]

59:27.355 --> 59:30.816
It's okay.
You're gonna
be all right now.

59:30.901 --> 59:32.985
[ Whimpering ]
Shh.

59:33.069 --> 59:37.239
Easy. Easy.
It's gonna be okay.

59:37.324 --> 59:39.825
It's all right.
You're gonna be okay.

59:39.910 --> 59:41.952
Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.

59:42.037 --> 59:45.122
Easy. Easy.

01:00:11.107 --> 01:00:13.692
[ Whirring ]

01:00:21.117 --> 01:00:23.619
What's her name again?
Rebecca.

01:00:23.703 --> 01:00:27.665
Now think, Rebecca.
Concentrate.

01:00:27.749 --> 01:00:30.584
Just start
at the beginning.

01:00:30.669 --> 01:00:33.712
Where are your parents?

01:00:33.797 --> 01:00:36.006
Now, look, Rebecca,
you have to try and help-

01:00:36.091 --> 01:00:38.717
Gorman, give it a rest,
why don't you?

01:00:41.054 --> 01:00:43.806
[ Sighs ]
Total brain lock.

01:00:43.890 --> 01:00:45.808
Physically, she's okay.

01:00:45.892 --> 01:00:49.103
Borderline malnutrition,
but I don't think there's
any permanent damage.

01:00:49.187 --> 01:00:51.605
Come on.
We're wasting our time.

01:01:01.157 --> 01:01:03.492
Try this.

01:01:03.577 --> 01:01:05.911
It's a little
hot chocolate.

01:01:07.414 --> 01:01:09.832
There you go.

01:01:09.916 --> 01:01:12.126
Whoop.

01:01:12.210 --> 01:01:14.169
That good, huh?

01:01:18.550 --> 01:01:22.011
Uh-oh. I made
a clean spot here.

01:01:22.095 --> 01:01:25.890
Now I've done it.
Guess l'll have to
do the whole thing.

01:01:35.442 --> 01:01:38.986
Hard to believe
there's a little girl
under all this.

01:01:40.989 --> 01:01:43.157
And a pretty one too.

01:01:47.203 --> 01:01:49.788
You don't talk much,
do you?

01:01:58.798 --> 01:02:00.758
Smoking
or nonsmoking?

01:02:00.842 --> 01:02:02.760
Just tell me what
you're scanning for, Private.

01:02:02.844 --> 01:02:04.762
P.D.T.s.
What?

01:02:04.846 --> 01:02:06.764
Personal data
transmitters.

01:02:06.848 --> 01:02:09.391
Every colonist had one
surgically implanted.

01:02:09.476 --> 01:02:12.645
If they're
within 20 klicks,
we'll read it out here.

01:02:12.729 --> 01:02:14.897
So far, zippo.

01:02:14.981 --> 01:02:17.900
I don't know how you
managed to stay alive,

01:02:17.984 --> 01:02:20.361
but you're one
brave kid, Rebecca.

01:02:22.364 --> 01:02:24.323
[ Whispers ]
N-Newt.

01:02:26.326 --> 01:02:29.828
- What'd you say?
- Newt.

01:02:29.913 --> 01:02:32.122
My name's Newt.

01:02:32.207 --> 01:02:37.336
Nobody calls me Rebecca
except my brother.

01:02:37.420 --> 01:02:41.298
Newt?
I like that.

01:02:41.383 --> 01:02:45.177
I'm Ripley.
It's nice to meet you.

01:02:47.180 --> 01:02:50.265
And who is this, hmm?

01:02:50.392 --> 01:02:54.103
Casey.
Hello, Casey.

01:02:54.187 --> 01:02:57.147
What about your brother?
What's his name?

01:02:57.232 --> 01:02:59.274
Timmy.

01:02:59.359 --> 01:03:03.821
Is Timmy around here too?
Maybe hiding like you were?

01:03:06.866 --> 01:03:08.826
Any sisters?

01:03:12.455 --> 01:03:14.373
Mom and dad?

01:03:17.210 --> 01:03:21.463
Newt, look at me.
Where are they?

01:03:21.548 --> 01:03:24.591
They're dead, all right?
Can I go now?

01:03:27.721 --> 01:03:30.180
I'm sorry, Newt.

01:03:30.265 --> 01:03:32.850
Don't you think you'd
be safer here with us?

01:03:36.730 --> 01:03:38.772
These people are here
to protect you.

01:03:38.857 --> 01:03:40.816
They're soldiers.

01:03:40.900 --> 01:03:43.736
It won't make
any difference.

01:03:51.119 --> 01:03:53.037
[ Door Opens ]

01:03:53.121 --> 01:03:55.080
[ Cart's Wheels Clacking ]

01:03:57.208 --> 01:03:59.251
Need anything else?

01:04:01.796 --> 01:04:04.757
Hello, Bishop. Do you
need anything else?

01:04:06.634 --> 01:04:08.677
No.

01:04:10.764 --> 01:04:12.890
That's a nice pet
you got there, Bishop.

01:04:12.974 --> 01:04:15.893
Magnificent, isn't it?

01:04:15.977 --> 01:04:20.981
Yo! Stop your grinnin'
and drop your linen! Found 'em.

01:04:21.107 --> 01:04:23.650
They alive?
Unknown,

01:04:23.735 --> 01:04:25.652
but it looks
like all of them.

01:04:25.737 --> 01:04:29.907
Over at the processing station,
Sublevel 3,

01:04:29.991 --> 01:04:32.451
under the main
cooling towers.

01:04:33.661 --> 01:04:36.288
Looks like
a goddamn town meeting.

01:04:36.372 --> 01:04:38.290
Let's saddle up, Apone.

01:04:38.374 --> 01:04:40.667
Aye, sir.

01:04:40.752 --> 01:04:43.337
All right. Let's go, people.
They ain't payin' us
by the hour.

01:04:43.421 --> 01:04:45.380
Let's go.
Head 'em out!

01:04:45.465 --> 01:04:47.466
Okay, Frost,
you're driving.

01:04:59.270 --> 01:05:02.731
It's okay. Don't worry.
It'll be okay.

01:05:43.273 --> 01:05:47.276
[ Gorman On Radio ] I want
a straight "V" deployment,
second team on left flank.

01:05:47.360 --> 01:05:51.405
Advance on axial 664.
Tracker on line.

01:05:51.489 --> 01:05:54.616
Set the "V" gain
to filter R.F. ambient.

01:05:54.701 --> 01:05:58.203
[ Apone ]
Hudson, tracker on line.
Left and right, little buddy.

01:05:58.288 --> 01:05:59.955
[ Clicking ]

01:06:00.039 --> 01:06:04.209
[ Gorman ]
Forty meters in, bearing 221 ,
there should be a stairwell.

01:06:04.294 --> 01:06:06.253
Check. Got it.

01:06:07.714 --> 01:06:09.631
[ Gorman ]
You want Sublevel 3.

01:06:11.843 --> 01:06:14.094
[ Apone ]
Let's go, people.
Hudson, you got the point.

01:06:14.179 --> 01:06:16.555
Hicks, watch our tails.

01:06:16.639 --> 01:06:19.808
Nice and easy.
Check those corners.

01:06:19.893 --> 01:06:22.144
Check those corners.

01:06:25.523 --> 01:06:28.150
Watch your spacing.
[ Apone ] All right.
You heard the man.

01:06:28.234 --> 01:06:30.152
Don't bunch up.
Stay loose.

01:06:30.236 --> 01:06:32.988
[ Gorman ]
Uh, your transmission's
showing a lot ofbreakup.

01:06:33.072 --> 01:06:37.284
[ Hudson ] Probably
getting some interference
from the structure.

01:06:37.368 --> 01:06:39.494
[ Apone ]
Use those lights.

01:06:39.579 --> 01:06:43.957
[ Gorman ]
Next one down,
and proceed on a 216.

01:06:44.042 --> 01:06:46.210
[Apone ]
Uh, roger. That's a 216.

01:06:48.421 --> 01:06:51.423
[ Gorman ]
I'm not making that out
too well. What is it, Hudson?

01:06:51.507 --> 01:06:54.468
You tell me, man.
I only work here.

01:07:09.567 --> 01:07:11.652
What is that?

01:07:11.736 --> 01:07:13.946
I don't know.

01:07:15.657 --> 01:07:17.950
Proceed inside.

01:07:33.758 --> 01:07:36.635
[ Apone On Headset ]
Watch your fire
and check your targets.

01:07:36.719 --> 01:07:39.054
Remember we're looking
for civvies in here.

01:07:48.856 --> 01:07:50.774
[ Apone ]
Easy.

01:07:50.858 --> 01:07:53.318
[ Hicks ]
Tighten it up, Frost.
We're getting a little thin.

01:07:55.113 --> 01:07:57.406
[Apone ]
Nice and easy.

01:07:59.701 --> 01:08:01.618
Looks like some sort
of secreted resin.

01:08:01.703 --> 01:08:05.497
Yeah, but secreted
from what?

01:08:05.581 --> 01:08:08.250
Nobody touch nothing.

01:08:08.334 --> 01:08:11.295
Busy little
creatures, huh?

01:08:11.379 --> 01:08:13.630
Hot as hell in here.

01:08:13.715 --> 01:08:15.632
Yeah, man,
but it's a dry heat.

01:08:15.717 --> 01:08:17.676
[Apone ]
Knock it off, Hudson.

01:08:25.600 --> 01:08:28.937
Lieutenant, what do
those pulse rifles fire?

01:08:29.022 --> 01:08:31.398
Ten millimeter
explosive-tip caseless.

01:08:31.482 --> 01:08:33.442
Standard light
armor-piercing round.

01:08:33.526 --> 01:08:35.777
Why?
Well, look where
your team is.

01:08:35.862 --> 01:08:39.113
They're right under
the primary
heat exchangers.

01:08:39.198 --> 01:08:41.198
So?

01:08:41.283 --> 01:08:44.995
So if they fire their weapons
in there, won't they rupture
the cooling system?

01:08:45.078 --> 01:08:49.332
- Ho, ho, ho. Yeah.
She's absolutely right.
- So? So what?

01:08:49.417 --> 01:08:53.627
Look. This whole station is
basically a big fusion reactor.

01:08:53.712 --> 01:08:56.089
Right?

01:08:56.174 --> 01:09:00.844
So you're talking about
a thermonuclear explosion,
and adios, muchachos.

01:09:00.928 --> 01:09:03.555
Oh, great. Wonderful.

01:09:03.639 --> 01:09:06.433
Shit!

01:09:08.394 --> 01:09:12.229
Look.
Uh... Apone.

01:09:12.314 --> 01:09:13.482
[ Snapping Fingers ]

01:09:13.566 --> 01:09:16.984
Look. We can't have
any firing in there.

01:09:17.069 --> 01:09:20.822
I, uh, I want you to collect
magazines from everybody.

01:09:20.907 --> 01:09:24.951
- Is he fuckin' crazy?
- What the hell are we supposed
to use, man, harsh language?

01:09:25.036 --> 01:09:27.871
- Flame units only.
I want rifles slung.
- Sir, I-

01:09:27.955 --> 01:09:30.916
Just do it, Sergeant.
And no grenades.

01:09:32.627 --> 01:09:36.712
All right, sweethearts.
You heard the man. Pull 'em out.
Come on. Let's have 'em.

01:09:37.715 --> 01:09:40.425
Come on, Vasquez.
Clear and lock.

01:09:43.304 --> 01:09:45.596
Damn!

01:09:45.680 --> 01:09:47.808
You too. Give it up, Ski.
Come on. Let's go.

01:09:47.892 --> 01:09:50.852
Crowe, I want it now.
Give it up.

01:09:50.937 --> 01:09:52.895
Right on, Vas.

01:09:54.148 --> 01:09:56.066
Let's go, marine.
Give it up.

01:09:56.150 --> 01:09:58.276
Frost, you got the duty.
Open that bag.

01:09:58.361 --> 01:10:01.238
- Thanks a lot, Sarge.
- Hicks, cover our ass.

01:10:01.322 --> 01:10:03.240
Head 'em out, people.

01:10:05.326 --> 01:10:08.912
I like to keep this handy...
for close encounters.

01:10:08.996 --> 01:10:10.914
I heard that.

01:10:10.998 --> 01:10:12.958
[ Tracker Clicking ]

01:10:19.841 --> 01:10:21.758
[ Gorman ]
Any movement?

01:10:21.843 --> 01:10:24.511
Nothing. Zip.

01:10:37.233 --> 01:10:39.651
Holy shit.

01:10:52.457 --> 01:10:54.958
[ Ripley ]
Newt, go sit up front.

01:10:55.042 --> 01:10:57.544
Go on! Now!

01:11:26.199 --> 01:11:28.950
[ Apone ]
Steady, people.
Let's finish our sweep.

01:11:29.035 --> 01:11:32.454
We're still marines,
and we got a job to do.

01:11:32.538 --> 01:11:36.249
Keep it moving. Easy.

01:12:08.241 --> 01:12:09.866
- Help!
- What?

01:12:09.951 --> 01:12:12.702
Top, get over here.
We got a live one!
You're gonna be all right.

01:12:12.787 --> 01:12:15.956
Please... k-kill me.

01:12:16.040 --> 01:12:18.917
[ Dietrich ]
Just stay calm.
We're gonna get you outta here.

01:12:19.001 --> 01:12:21.586
It's gonna be all right.
Give me a hand.
We gotta get her outta here.

01:12:21.671 --> 01:12:24.047
- What is it, Dietrich?
- Convulsion!

01:12:24.131 --> 01:12:26.800
- [ Screaming ]
- Dietrich, get back!

01:12:26.884 --> 01:12:29.261
- Get back!
- [ Screams ]

01:12:36.394 --> 01:12:39.688
- No!
- Frost, flamethrower.
Kill it!

01:12:39.772 --> 01:12:42.399
Get back!
Flamethrower! Move!

01:12:42.483 --> 01:12:45.110
[ Alien Screeches ]

01:12:47.905 --> 01:12:51.908
- [ Groaning ]
- [ Screeching ]

01:12:51.993 --> 01:12:53.660
[ Hissing ]

01:13:12.221 --> 01:13:13.930
[ Tracker Beeping ]
Movement!

01:13:14.015 --> 01:13:18.768
- What's the position?
- I can't lock in!

01:13:18.853 --> 01:13:21.229
Talk to me, Hudson!

01:13:21.314 --> 01:13:24.482
Multiple signals.

01:13:24.567 --> 01:13:26.693
They're closing.

01:13:26.777 --> 01:13:30.071
Go to infrared, people.
Look sharp!

01:13:30.156 --> 01:13:33.491
What's happening, Apone?
Can't see anything in here.

01:13:33.576 --> 01:13:35.493
Pull your team out,
Gorman.

01:13:41.334 --> 01:13:44.085
I got signals.
I got readings
in front and behind.

01:13:44.170 --> 01:13:46.379
Where, man?
I don't see shit.

01:13:46.464 --> 01:13:48.965
He's right.
There's nothing back here.

01:13:49.050 --> 01:13:51.509
Look, I'm telling you.
There's something moving,
and it ain't us!

01:13:53.554 --> 01:13:56.556
- Oh, shit.
- [ Hudson ]
Tracker's off scale, man.

01:13:56.641 --> 01:13:59.934
They're all
around us, man! Jesus!

01:14:00.019 --> 01:14:02.937
Maybe they don't show up
on infrared at all.

01:14:06.609 --> 01:14:08.652
[ Screams ]

01:14:10.321 --> 01:14:13.114
[ Screaming ]

01:14:13.199 --> 01:14:15.659
- Frost!
- [ Screams ]

01:14:19.789 --> 01:14:21.748
Come on!

01:14:28.214 --> 01:14:30.799
- [ Steady Beep ]
- Jesus Christ, Apone!
What is going on?

01:14:30.883 --> 01:14:33.802
[ Hicks ]
Wierzbowski
and Crowe are down!

01:14:33.928 --> 01:14:37.931
Dietrich, Crowe!
Sound off! Frost!
Dietrich, Frost, off the board!

01:14:39.350 --> 01:14:40.600
Frost!

01:14:42.269 --> 01:14:45.814
[ Man Screaming ]
Wierzbowski?

01:14:45.898 --> 01:14:48.608
- Wierzbowski?
- [ Wierzbowski Screaming ]

01:14:48.734 --> 01:14:52.404
[ Grunts ]
Let's rock!
[ Drake Shouting ]

01:14:52.488 --> 01:14:55.031
[ Gunfire ]

01:14:55.116 --> 01:14:56.741
Who's firing?
Goddamn it!

01:14:57.743 --> 01:14:58.952
Yeah!

01:14:59.078 --> 01:15:03.123
I ordered to hold fire.
[ Hudson ] They're coming
out of the walls!

01:15:03.207 --> 01:15:05.542
They're coming out
of the goddamn walls!
Let's book!

01:15:05.668 --> 01:15:07.877
[ Vasquez ]
On the right, man.
Uh, Apone,

01:15:07.962 --> 01:15:10.714
I want you to lay down
a suppressing fire with the incinerators-

01:15:10.798 --> 01:15:13.550
Vasquez, Drake,
hold your fire,
goddamn it!

01:15:13.634 --> 01:15:17.554
[ Gorman ] Apone, are you
copying me? I want you
to lay down suppressing fire...

01:15:17.638 --> 01:15:20.140
with the incinerators
and fall back by squads
to the A.P.C.

01:15:20.266 --> 01:15:22.642
Over.
Say again,
all after "incinerator."

01:15:22.727 --> 01:15:27.397
I said I want you to lay down
a suppressing fire with
the incinerators and fall back...

01:15:27.523 --> 01:15:30.066
by squads to the A.P.C.
Over.
[ Gunfire ]

01:15:30.985 --> 01:15:32.026
Hey!

01:15:32.111 --> 01:15:33.903
[ Screaming ]

01:15:33.988 --> 01:15:36.406
- [ Hudson ] Sarge! Sarge!
- Apone.

01:15:36.490 --> 01:15:38.908
Talk to me. Apone?
Copy! Copy!

01:15:38.993 --> 01:15:41.286
Talk to me, Apone.
He's gone!

01:15:42.955 --> 01:15:45.331
Get them out of there!
Shut up!

01:15:45.458 --> 01:15:48.334
Do it now! Hicks,
whoever's left, get-
Shut up!

01:15:48.461 --> 01:15:50.336
Just shut up!
Goddamn it!

01:15:50.463 --> 01:15:54.883
It's coming out of
the goddamn walls!
Where's Apone? Where's Apone?

01:15:54.967 --> 01:15:57.260
The sarge is gone!
Let's get the fuck out of here!

01:15:57.344 --> 01:16:01.139
Let's move it!
Let's go, marine!

01:16:01.223 --> 01:16:04.309
Hudson? Vasquez?

01:16:04.435 --> 01:16:07.520
Hudson, look out!
Get it!

01:16:08.647 --> 01:16:10.648
[ Alien Screeching ]
Watch it!

01:16:10.733 --> 01:16:13.109
Hicks.
Come on. Behind you!
Fall back!

01:16:13.235 --> 01:16:16.696
I told them to fall back.
[ Hicks ]
Fall back, goddamn it, now!

01:16:16.822 --> 01:16:18.698
They're cut off!
[ Hicks ]
Hudson, move your ass!

01:16:18.824 --> 01:16:20.700
Do something!
[ Hicks ] Let's go, marine!

01:16:20.785 --> 01:16:22.744
Fuck!

01:16:22.870 --> 01:16:25.830
Come on.
Keep moving, baby.
Hold on, Newt.

01:16:28.793 --> 01:16:31.544
[ Engines Revving ]

01:16:31.629 --> 01:16:34.881
Ripley, what the hell
are you doing?

01:16:34.965 --> 01:16:37.342
[ Tires Squealing ]

01:16:40.805 --> 01:16:42.514
Turn around!

01:16:45.893 --> 01:16:48.269
That's an order!

01:16:51.774 --> 01:16:55.235
Get offme, damn it!
Goddamn it, that's an order!

01:16:55.319 --> 01:16:58.029
You had your chance,
Gorman.

01:17:01.283 --> 01:17:03.535
[ Tires Squealing ]

01:17:09.375 --> 01:17:11.292
Come on!

01:17:30.855 --> 01:17:33.481
- Come on. Let's move it!
- [ Screeches ]

01:17:33.566 --> 01:17:35.900
[ Vasquez ] Come on!
Let's go! Let's go!

01:17:35.985 --> 01:17:39.445
[ Hudson ] It's blocked, man.
We gotta go around!

01:17:39.530 --> 01:17:44.325
- Open the door! Hicks!
- Drake, we are leaving!

01:17:44.410 --> 01:17:46.411
[ Drake ]
Get them, man!

01:17:47.288 --> 01:17:49.873
Run for it!

01:17:50.958 --> 01:17:53.418
Shit!
[ Grunting ]

01:17:56.171 --> 01:17:59.424
[ Grunts ]
Go! Go!
[ Vasquez ] Come on, man! Come on!

01:18:07.516 --> 01:18:11.394
- Drake, come on!
- [ Screeches ]

01:18:13.939 --> 01:18:16.149
- [ Screams ]
- No!

01:18:18.235 --> 01:18:21.070
- Fire in the hole!
- [ Hicks ] He's gone!

01:18:21.155 --> 01:18:23.031
Put it out! Put it out!
Go! Go!

01:18:23.115 --> 01:18:26.826
- Come on. Put it out!
- Drake's coming, man!

01:18:26.952 --> 01:18:29.913
Drake!
No, he's not!
He's gone!

01:18:31.332 --> 01:18:33.291
Forget him!
He's gone!

01:18:39.131 --> 01:18:41.049
They're in the goddamn door!

01:18:44.470 --> 01:18:47.180
Eat this!

01:18:47.264 --> 01:18:50.350
- [ Screaming ]
- [ Hicks ] Ripley!

01:18:50.434 --> 01:18:52.769
Go, go, go!

01:19:26.095 --> 01:19:28.429
[ Clatter]

01:19:55.541 --> 01:19:57.458
It's all right!
We're clear!
[ Metal Clattering ]

01:19:57.543 --> 01:19:59.961
Ripley, you've blown
the transaxle!

01:20:00.045 --> 01:20:01.963
You're just
grinding metal!

01:20:02.047 --> 01:20:04.257
Come on, ease down.

01:20:04.341 --> 01:20:06.384
Ease down.

01:20:06.468 --> 01:20:10.221
Ease down. Ease down.
Ease down.

01:20:17.730 --> 01:20:19.731
[ Newt Coughing ]

01:20:21.900 --> 01:20:24.152
You okay?

01:20:25.529 --> 01:20:27.572
l'm all right.
Hudson.

01:20:27.656 --> 01:20:29.699
Get away from me, man!

01:20:29.825 --> 01:20:33.828
Lieutenant.
What happened
to Gorman?

01:20:33.912 --> 01:20:37.165
I don't know.
Maybe a concussion.

01:20:37.249 --> 01:20:39.542
But he's alive.
He's dead!

01:20:39.626 --> 01:20:41.711
Wake up, pendejo, and then
I'm gonna kill you!

01:20:41.795 --> 01:20:45.006
Back off.
Right now.

01:20:46.467 --> 01:20:49.635
Fuck!
Somebody get me
a first aid kit.

01:20:49.720 --> 01:20:52.847
Hey. Hey, look.

01:20:52.931 --> 01:20:56.225
The sarge and Dietrich
aren't dead, man.

01:20:56.310 --> 01:20:58.311
Their signs are real low,
but they ain't dead.

01:20:58.395 --> 01:21:00.646
- Then we go back
in there and get them.
- Fuck that!

01:21:00.773 --> 01:21:03.149
We don't leave our people behind
I ain't going back in there.

01:21:03.233 --> 01:21:05.693
You can't help them!

01:21:05.778 --> 01:21:10.448
You can't. Right now
they're being cocooned
just like the others.

01:21:14.745 --> 01:21:18.998
Oh, dear Lord Jesus,
this ain't happenin', man.
Damn it.

01:21:19.083 --> 01:21:22.168
This can't be happenin', man.
This isn't happenin'!

01:21:22.252 --> 01:21:25.797
All right. We got
seven canisters of CN-20.

01:21:25.881 --> 01:21:29.217
I say we roll them in there
and nerve gas
the whole fucking nest.

01:21:29.301 --> 01:21:32.095
That's worth a try,
but we don't even know
if it's gonna affect them.

01:21:32.179 --> 01:21:36.641
Let's just bug out and call it
even. Okay? What are we
talking about this for?

01:21:36.725 --> 01:21:40.436
I say we take off
and nuke the entire
site from orbit.

01:21:43.315 --> 01:21:45.233
It's the only way
to be sure.

01:21:45.317 --> 01:21:48.569
Fuckin' "A"!
Hold on.
Hold on one second.

01:21:48.654 --> 01:21:52.824
This installation has
a substantial dollar value
attached to it.

01:21:52.908 --> 01:21:55.409
They can bill me.

01:21:55.494 --> 01:22:00.540
Okay, look.
This is an emotional moment
for all of us, okay?

01:22:00.624 --> 01:22:04.043
I know that.
But let's not make
snap judgments, please.

01:22:04.128 --> 01:22:07.088
This is clearly-
clearly an important species
we're dealing with,

01:22:07.172 --> 01:22:09.924
and I don't think that
you or I or anybody
has the right...

01:22:10.008 --> 01:22:13.094
- to arbitrarily
exterminate them.
- Wrong.

01:22:13.178 --> 01:22:14.720
Yeah. Watch us.

01:22:14.805 --> 01:22:17.098
Maybe you haven't been
keeping up on current events,

01:22:17.182 --> 01:22:19.851
but we just got
our asses kicked, pal!

01:22:19.935 --> 01:22:23.271
Look. I'm not blind
to what's going on,

01:22:23.355 --> 01:22:25.940
but I cannot authorize
that kind of action.

01:22:26.024 --> 01:22:28.109
I'm sorry.

01:22:29.236 --> 01:22:32.155
Well, I believe
Corporal Hicks...

01:22:32.239 --> 01:22:34.198
has authority here.

01:22:35.701 --> 01:22:37.618
Corporal Hicks is-

01:22:37.703 --> 01:22:40.079
This operation
is under military
jurisdiction,

01:22:40.164 --> 01:22:42.081
and Hicks is next
in chain of command.

01:22:42.166 --> 01:22:44.333
Am I right, Corporal?

01:22:44.418 --> 01:22:46.377
Yeah.

01:22:47.546 --> 01:22:50.047
Yeah, that's right.

01:22:50.174 --> 01:22:52.216
Yeah. Look, Ripley.
Yes.

01:22:52.301 --> 01:22:54.760
This is a multimillion-dollar
installation, okay?

01:22:54.845 --> 01:22:56.762
He can't make
that kind of decision.

01:22:56.847 --> 01:22:59.432
He's just a grunt.
Uh, no offense.

01:22:59.516 --> 01:23:03.269
None taken.
Ferro, do you copy?
Standing by.

01:23:03.353 --> 01:23:06.022
Prep for dust off.
We're gonna need
immediate evac.

01:23:06.106 --> 01:23:08.024
Roger. On our way.

01:23:08.108 --> 01:23:12.737
I say we take off,
nuke the site from orbit.
It's the only way to be sure.

01:23:15.365 --> 01:23:17.116
Let's do it.

01:23:17.201 --> 01:23:21.078
[ Wind Whistling ]

01:23:24.208 --> 01:23:27.752
Let's go.
Pick it up, Hudson.
Pick it up, baby.

01:23:32.966 --> 01:23:35.134
All right.
Set him down here.

01:23:41.725 --> 01:23:43.768
Move it, Spunkmeyer.
We're rolling.

01:23:48.941 --> 01:23:50.858
Hold on a second.
There's something-

01:23:50.943 --> 01:23:53.236
[ Ferro ]
Just get up here.

01:23:53.320 --> 01:23:55.821
I'm in. Ramp closing.

01:24:15.550 --> 01:24:17.510
Spunkmeyer.

01:24:18.720 --> 01:24:22.390
Goddamn it.
[ Door Opens ]

01:24:22.474 --> 01:24:24.809
Well, where the fuck-

01:24:24.893 --> 01:24:27.019
[ Hisses ]

01:24:37.572 --> 01:24:39.490
Run!

01:25:20.365 --> 01:25:24.160
Well, that's great.
That's just fuckin' great, man.

01:25:24.244 --> 01:25:26.704
Now what the fuck
are we supposed to do?

01:25:26.788 --> 01:25:29.081
We're in some
real pretty shit now, man!

01:25:29.166 --> 01:25:31.542
Are you finished?

01:25:34.379 --> 01:25:36.339
You all right?

01:25:41.553 --> 01:25:45.765
I guess we're not gonna
be leaving now, right?

01:25:45.849 --> 01:25:47.433
I'm sorry, Newt.

01:25:47.559 --> 01:25:51.479
You don't have to be sorry.
It wasn't your fault.
That's it, man.

01:25:51.563 --> 01:25:53.939
Game over, man!
Game over!

01:25:54.024 --> 01:25:56.650
What the fuck
are we gonna do now?
What are we gonna do?

01:25:56.735 --> 01:26:01.155
Maybe we could build a fire.
Sing a couple of songs, huh?
Why don't we try that?

01:26:01.239 --> 01:26:03.991
We'd better get back
'cause it'll be dark soon,

01:26:04.076 --> 01:26:07.453
and they mostly
come at night, mostly.

01:26:24.262 --> 01:26:28.265
That's everything, right?
All right. This is
absolutely everything...

01:26:28.350 --> 01:26:31.352
that we could salvage
out of the A.P.C. wreckage.

01:26:31.436 --> 01:26:35.022
We got four pulse rifles
with about 50 rounds each.

01:26:35.107 --> 01:26:37.233
That ain't so good.

01:26:37.317 --> 01:26:41.028
We got, uh,
1 5 of these M-40 grenades.

01:26:41.113 --> 01:26:43.030
Don't touch that.

01:26:43.156 --> 01:26:45.616
Dangerous, honey.
Is that the only
flamethrower?

01:26:45.700 --> 01:26:49.745
[ Hicks ]
Yeah. It's only half full,
but it's functional.

01:26:49.830 --> 01:26:53.582
Got another one, it's damaged
I don't know about that one.

01:26:53.667 --> 01:26:59.463
But the good news-
we got four of these
robot sentries,

01:26:59.548 --> 01:27:02.591
with display
and scanners intact.

01:27:02.676 --> 01:27:05.845
They really kick ass.
I think they'll come in handy.

01:27:05.929 --> 01:27:10.349
How long after
we're declared overdue
can we expect a rescue?

01:27:12.394 --> 01:27:14.520
Seventeen days.

01:27:15.522 --> 01:27:18.065
Seventeen days?

01:27:18.150 --> 01:27:22.027
Hey, man, I don't wanna rain
on your parade, but we're
not gonna last 17 hours.

01:27:22.112 --> 01:27:25.739
Those things are gonna come in
here like they did before.
They're gonna come in here-

01:27:25.866 --> 01:27:28.951
Hudson! Hudson!
They're gonna come in here
and they're gonna get us!

01:27:29.035 --> 01:27:31.078
This little girl
survived longer than that...

01:27:31.163 --> 01:27:34.206
with no weapons
and no training.

01:27:34.291 --> 01:27:36.208
Right?

01:27:38.587 --> 01:27:41.297
Why don't you
put her in charge?

01:27:41.381 --> 01:27:44.216
You'd better just start
dealing with it, Hudson.
Listen to me.

01:27:44.301 --> 01:27:46.469
Hudson, just deal with it
because we need you.

01:27:46.553 --> 01:27:48.471
And I'm sick
of your bullshit.

01:27:48.555 --> 01:27:52.141
Now, I want you to get on
a terminal and call up
some kind of floor plan file.

01:27:52.225 --> 01:27:54.935
Do you understand?
Construction blueprints.
I don't care.

01:27:55.020 --> 01:27:57.354
Anything that shows
the layout of this place.
Are you listening?

01:27:57.481 --> 01:28:00.566
Yeah.
I need to see air ducts.

01:28:00.650 --> 01:28:04.028
I need to see
electrical access tunnels,
subbasements,

01:28:04.112 --> 01:28:07.823
every possible way
into this complex.

01:28:07.908 --> 01:28:12.369
- We don't have much time.
- Okay.

01:28:12.496 --> 01:28:14.788
Okay, I'm on it.
Hudson!

01:28:14.873 --> 01:28:19.543
- Just relax.
- [ Exhales Sharply ]

01:28:22.964 --> 01:28:28.010
I'll be in medlab.
I'll check on Gorman,
continue my analysis.

01:28:28.094 --> 01:28:31.013
Fine.
You do that.

01:28:37.229 --> 01:28:41.065
So this service tunnel
must be how they're moving
back and forth.

01:28:41.149 --> 01:28:43.651
That's right.
It moves from
the processing station...

01:28:43.735 --> 01:28:46.070
right into
the sublevel here.

01:28:48.114 --> 01:28:51.450
Come down on that.
Okay, come over.

01:28:51.535 --> 01:28:54.745
Hold. Go back.
Okay, punch that in
right there.

01:29:00.418 --> 01:29:02.461
No. It's back here.
Okay.

01:29:04.005 --> 01:29:06.632
Well, there's
a pressure door
at this end.

01:29:06.758 --> 01:29:11.387
Couldn't we put one of
the remote sentry units
in the tunnel and then seal that door?

01:29:11.471 --> 01:29:14.473
Yeah, that'll work,
but we gotta figure on them
getting into the complex.

01:29:14.558 --> 01:29:19.562
That's right,
so we repair the barricades
at these two intersections.

01:29:19.688 --> 01:29:22.356
Right.
And weld plate steel
over these ducts...

01:29:22.440 --> 01:29:26.819
here and here and here.

01:29:26.903 --> 01:29:29.905
That way they can
only come at us
from these two corridors.

01:29:29.990 --> 01:29:35.661
All right. Then we put
the other sentry units
here and here, right?

01:29:35.787 --> 01:29:38.247
Right.
Outstanding.

01:29:38.331 --> 01:29:40.291
Now all we need
is a deck of cards.

01:29:42.586 --> 01:29:44.670
All right, people.
Let's move like
we got a purpose.

01:29:44.796 --> 01:29:47.548
[ Hudson ]
Affirmative.
Affirmative.

01:29:59.144 --> 01:30:02.730
[ Beeping ]

01:30:02.814 --> 01:30:06.483
Do your thing, baby.
Come on, Vasquez.
Let's get the hell outta here.

01:30:06.568 --> 01:30:09.445
Hudson here.
"A" and "B" sentries
are in place and keyed.

01:30:09.529 --> 01:30:14.366
Roger. Stand by.
Arming now.
Test it, Hudson.

01:30:14.492 --> 01:30:16.869
Do it!
Fire in the hole!

01:30:20.123 --> 01:30:22.916
Okay, great.
Let's get the hell
outta here!

01:30:23.001 --> 01:30:26.462
We're sealing the tunnel.
Come on, baby.

01:30:28.506 --> 01:30:30.341
[ Welder Crackling ]

01:30:38.642 --> 01:30:40.559
For what it's worth.

01:30:42.520 --> 01:30:44.813
Here. I want you
to put this on.

01:30:46.191 --> 01:30:48.442
- What's it for?
- It's a locator.

01:30:48.526 --> 01:30:51.987
Then I can find you
anywhere in the complex
on this.

01:30:52.072 --> 01:30:53.697
[ Beeping ]

01:30:53.823 --> 01:30:57.910
It's just
a precaution.
Thanks.

01:30:57.994 --> 01:31:00.788
Doesn't mean we're
engaged or anything.

01:31:00.872 --> 01:31:02.873
All right,
what's next?

01:31:09.714 --> 01:31:13.759
[ Beeping ]

01:31:27.399 --> 01:31:29.983
[ Door Closes ]

01:31:32.487 --> 01:31:34.530
Last stop.

01:31:38.535 --> 01:31:40.452
Get in.

01:31:40.537 --> 01:31:44.623
Scoot down.
That's good.

01:31:44.708 --> 01:31:48.752
Now, you lie here
and have a nap.
You're very tired.

01:31:48.837 --> 01:31:52.214
I don't want to.
I have scary dreams.

01:31:54.592 --> 01:31:57.678
Well, I bet Casey doesn't
have scary dreams.

01:31:57.762 --> 01:31:59.680
Let's take a look.

01:31:59.764 --> 01:32:02.099
Nope. Nothing bad
in there.

01:32:02.183 --> 01:32:06.478
See? Maybe you could
just try to be like her, hmm?

01:32:06.563 --> 01:32:09.064
Ripley, she doesn't
have bad dreams...

01:32:09.149 --> 01:32:12.192
because she's just
a piece of plastic.

01:32:12.277 --> 01:32:15.779
Right.
I'm sorry, Newt.

01:32:22.495 --> 01:32:24.747
There.

01:32:24.831 --> 01:32:27.708
My mommy always said
there were no monsters-

01:32:27.792 --> 01:32:31.128
no real ones-
but there are.

01:32:32.464 --> 01:32:34.423
Yes, there are,
aren't there?

01:32:36.509 --> 01:32:38.844
Why do they tell
little kids that?

01:32:40.722 --> 01:32:42.639
Most of the time
it's true.

01:32:42.724 --> 01:32:46.185
Did one of those things
grow inside her?

01:32:46.269 --> 01:32:49.062
I don't know, Newt.

01:32:49.147 --> 01:32:51.106
That's the truth.

01:32:51.191 --> 01:32:55.778
Isn't that how babies come?
I mean, people babies?

01:32:55.904 --> 01:32:59.448
They grow inside you.
Oh, that's very different.

01:32:59.532 --> 01:33:01.450
Did you ever
have a baby?

01:33:01.534 --> 01:33:04.828
Yes, I did.
I had a little girl.

01:33:04.954 --> 01:33:09.500
Where is she?
She's gone.

01:33:11.336 --> 01:33:13.295
You mean dead.

01:33:14.881 --> 01:33:15.839
Here.

01:33:17.217 --> 01:33:19.051
Take this.

01:33:20.553 --> 01:33:22.513
For luck.

01:33:25.725 --> 01:33:27.684
There's that.

01:33:29.854 --> 01:33:31.772
Don't go, please.

01:33:31.856 --> 01:33:35.400
Newt, I'm gonna be
right in the next room.

01:33:35.485 --> 01:33:37.402
And you see that camera
right up there?

01:33:37.487 --> 01:33:40.280
I can see you
right through that camera,

01:33:40.365 --> 01:33:42.699
all the time
to see if you're safe.

01:33:47.080 --> 01:33:49.748
I'm not gonna
leave you, Newt.

01:33:49.833 --> 01:33:53.752
I mean that.
That's a promise.

01:33:53.837 --> 01:33:56.505
You promise?

01:33:56.589 --> 01:33:58.882
I cross my heart.

01:33:58.967 --> 01:34:03.262
- And hope to die?
- And hope to die.

01:34:12.230 --> 01:34:14.189
[ Kisses ]

01:34:18.152 --> 01:34:22.614
Now go to sleep,
and don't dream.

01:34:23.741 --> 01:34:25.742
[ Laughs ]

01:34:26.786 --> 01:34:28.745
Sneak.

01:34:33.585 --> 01:34:36.086
[ Door Opens ]

01:34:37.505 --> 01:34:41.758
The molecular acid oxidizes
after the creature's death,
completely neutralizing it.

01:34:41.843 --> 01:34:45.262
Bishop, you know, that's
very interesting, but it doesn't
really get us anywhere, does it?

01:34:45.346 --> 01:34:47.890
I'm trying to figure out
what we're dealing with here.

01:34:47.974 --> 01:34:50.058
Let's go through it again.

01:34:50.143 --> 01:34:52.352
They grab the colonists,
they move them over there...

01:34:52.437 --> 01:34:56.773
and they immobilize them
to be hosts for more of these.

01:34:56.858 --> 01:35:00.694
Which would mean that
there would have to be
a lot of these parasites, right?

01:35:00.778 --> 01:35:02.946
One for each colonist.
That's over 100, at least.

01:35:03.031 --> 01:35:04.948
Yes. hat follows.

01:35:05.033 --> 01:35:09.077
But each one of these things
comes from an egg, right?

01:35:11.623 --> 01:35:13.540
So who's laying
these eggs?

01:35:13.625 --> 01:35:16.710
I'm not sure.

01:35:16.794 --> 01:35:18.754
It must be something
we haven't seen yet.

01:35:18.838 --> 01:35:21.048
Hey, maybe it's like
an ant hive.

01:35:21.132 --> 01:35:23.175
Bees, man.
Bees have hives.

01:35:23.259 --> 01:35:28.388
You know what I mean.
There's, like, one female
that runs the whole show.

01:35:28.514 --> 01:35:30.891
Yes, the queen.
Ueah, the mama.

01:35:30.975 --> 01:35:33.310
She's badass, man.
I mean, big.

01:35:33.436 --> 01:35:35.979
These things ain't ants,
estpido.
I know that.

01:35:36.064 --> 01:35:40.734
Bishop, I want these specimens
destroyed as soon as
you're finished with them.

01:35:40.818 --> 01:35:43.737
- Is that clear?
- Mr. Burke gave instructions...

01:35:43.821 --> 01:35:47.658
that they were to be kept alive
in stasis for return
to the company labs.

01:35:49.869 --> 01:35:51.828
He was very specific
about it.

01:35:53.247 --> 01:35:57.250
Look. Those two specimens
are worth millions
to the bio-weapons division, right?

01:35:57.335 --> 01:36:00.712
Now, if you're smart,
we can both come out
of this heroes,

01:36:00.797 --> 01:36:04.007
and we will be
set up for life.

01:36:05.051 --> 01:36:07.636
You're crazy, Burke.
Do you know that?

01:36:07.720 --> 01:36:11.890
Do you really think you can get
a dangerous organism like that
past I.C.C. quarantine?

01:36:11.974 --> 01:36:14.851
How can they impound it
if they don't
know about it?

01:36:14.936 --> 01:36:17.979
But they will know about it,
Burke, from me.

01:36:18.064 --> 01:36:22.275
Just like they'll know
that you were responsible
for the deaths of 157 colonists.

01:36:22.402 --> 01:36:24.820
Wait a second.
You sent them
to that ship.

01:36:24.946 --> 01:36:27.030
You're wrong.
I just checked
the colony log.

01:36:27.115 --> 01:36:30.992
Directive dated 6-1 2-79,
signed Burke, Carter J.

01:36:31.077 --> 01:36:33.995
You sent them out there,
and you didn't even warn them.

01:36:34.122 --> 01:36:36.540
Why didn't you
warn them, Burke?
Okay, look.

01:36:36.624 --> 01:36:39.126
What if that ship
didn't even exist?
Do you ever think about that?

01:36:39.210 --> 01:36:42.879
I didn't know. So now
if I went and made a major
security situation out of it,

01:36:43.005 --> 01:36:46.383
everybody steps in,
administration steps in, and
there's no exclusive rights for anybody.

01:36:46.467 --> 01:36:50.512
Nobody wins.
So I made a decision,
and it was wrong.

01:36:50.596 --> 01:36:53.306
It was a bad call, Ripley.
It was a bad call.

01:36:53.433 --> 01:36:55.100
Bad call?
Right.

01:36:55.184 --> 01:36:56.810
These people
are dead, Burke!

01:36:56.894 --> 01:36:59.312
Don't you have any idea
what you've done here?

01:36:59.397 --> 01:37:02.315
I'm gonna make sure
that they nail you
right to the wall for this!

01:37:02.400 --> 01:37:04.651
You're not gonna
sleaze your way
out of this one.

01:37:04.736 --> 01:37:06.903
Right to the wall.

01:37:08.740 --> 01:37:11.783
Ripley. I-

01:37:11.868 --> 01:37:13.869
You know, I expected
more from you.

01:37:13.953 --> 01:37:16.913
I thought you'd be
smarter than this.

01:37:16.998 --> 01:37:20.375
Well, I'm happy
to disappoint you.

01:37:27.175 --> 01:37:29.551
[Alarm Blaring ]

01:37:33.973 --> 01:37:36.349
- [ Hudson ]
What is it? What's going on?
- They're coming.

01:37:36.476 --> 01:37:38.935
Where?
In the tunnel.

01:37:39.020 --> 01:37:40.395
[Automatic Gunfire ]

01:37:40.480 --> 01:37:45.942
Here we go. "A" and "B"
gun tracking far end.
Multiple targets.

01:37:51.741 --> 01:37:53.617
Those ammo counters go.

01:37:56.287 --> 01:37:58.413
"B" gun's down 50%..

01:37:59.582 --> 01:38:01.833
Man, it's a shooting gallery
down there.

01:38:05.797 --> 01:38:07.547
- [ Hicks ]
Sixty rounds left on "B."
- [ Beeping ]

01:38:07.632 --> 01:38:10.801
Forty. Twenty. Ten.

01:38:10.885 --> 01:38:13.136
"B" gun's dry.
Twenty on "A."

01:38:14.388 --> 01:38:17.599
- Ten. Five.
- [ Steady Beep ]

01:38:20.478 --> 01:38:22.145
That's it.

01:38:22.230 --> 01:38:25.482
Jesus, they were
wall-to-wall in there.

01:38:26.484 --> 01:38:29.361
[ Pounding ]

01:38:29.445 --> 01:38:31.446
They're at
the pressure door.

01:38:33.032 --> 01:38:34.991
Man, listen to that.

01:38:35.076 --> 01:38:38.745
Bishop here.
I'm afraid I have
some bad news.

01:38:38.830 --> 01:38:39.412
Well, that's a switch.

01:38:42.917 --> 01:38:45.710
It's very pretty, Bishop,
but what are we looking for?

01:38:45.795 --> 01:38:49.339
That's it.
Emergency venting.

01:38:49.423 --> 01:38:54.052
Oh, that's beautiful, man.
Oh, man, that-
that just beats it all.

01:38:54.178 --> 01:38:57.013
How long till it blows?
Four hours.

01:38:57.139 --> 01:39:00.183
[ Groans ]
With a blast radius
of 30 kilometers,

01:39:00.268 --> 01:39:03.895
equal to about
40 megatons.

01:39:04.021 --> 01:39:07.482
We got problems.
[ Hudson ] I don't believe this.
I don't fucking believe this.

01:39:07.567 --> 01:39:10.068
Vasquez,
close the shutters.

01:39:10.152 --> 01:39:12.320
Why can't we shut it
down from here?

01:39:12.405 --> 01:39:14.322
I'm sorry.
The crash caused
too much damage.

01:39:14.407 --> 01:39:16.950
An overload is inevitable
at this point.

01:39:17.034 --> 01:39:19.953
Oh, man, and I was
getting short.

01:39:20.037 --> 01:39:23.373
Four more weeks and out.
Now l'm gonna buy it
on this rock.

01:39:23.499 --> 01:39:25.542
It ain't half fair, man.
Hudson, give us a break!

01:39:25.626 --> 01:39:28.211
[ Hudson ]
Four more weeks. Oh, man.

01:39:28.296 --> 01:39:31.506
We've got to get the other
drop ship from the Sulaco.

01:39:31.591 --> 01:39:34.551
I mean, there must be some way
of bringing it down on remote.

01:39:34.635 --> 01:39:38.138
How? The transmitter
was on the A.P.C.
It's wasted.

01:39:38.264 --> 01:39:41.474
I don't care how,
but we'd better think of something.
We'd better think of a way.

01:39:41.601 --> 01:39:44.436
Think of what?
We're fucked! We're doomed!
Shut up!

01:39:44.520 --> 01:39:47.314
Shut up! What about
the colony transmitters?

01:39:47.398 --> 01:39:50.191
The uplink tower
down at the other end.
Why can't we use that?

01:39:50.276 --> 01:39:53.236
No, I checked.
The hardware in between here
and there was damaged.

01:39:53.321 --> 01:39:55.238
We can't align the dish.

01:39:55.323 --> 01:39:57.741
Well, somebody's gonna
have to go out there,

01:39:57.825 --> 01:40:00.744
take a portable terminal,
go out there
and patch in manually.

01:40:00.828 --> 01:40:05.874
Oh, yeah, sure. With those
things running around?
You can count me out.

01:40:06.000 --> 01:40:08.001
Guess we can just
count you out of everything.
I'll go.

01:40:08.085 --> 01:40:09.878
[ Hudson ] That's right, man.
Why don't you go, man?

01:40:10.004 --> 01:40:11.838
[ Bishop ]
I'll go.
What?

01:40:11.923 --> 01:40:16.259
I'll go. I mean,
I'm the only one qualified
to remote pilot the ship anyway.

01:40:16.344 --> 01:40:20.722
Yeah, right, man.
Bishop should go.
Good idea.

01:40:20.806 --> 01:40:22.974
Believe me,
I'd prefer not to.

01:40:23.059 --> 01:40:25.977
I may be synthetic,
but I'm not stupid.

01:40:37.740 --> 01:40:39.658
[ Ripley]
How long?

01:40:39.742 --> 01:40:42.994
This conduit runs almost
to the uplink assembly-
1 80 meters.

01:40:43.120 --> 01:40:46.414
Say 40 minutes
to crawl down there-
[ Ripley ] Right.

01:40:46.499 --> 01:40:50.251
An hour to patch in
and align the antenna.

01:40:51.337 --> 01:40:53.588
Thirty minutes
to prep the ship,

01:40:53.714 --> 01:40:56.925
and about 50 minutes
flight time.
It's gonna be close.

01:41:01.430 --> 01:41:04.140
Good luck.
See you soon.

01:41:05.601 --> 01:41:09.396
Watch your fingers.
[ Grunts ]

01:41:10.398 --> 01:41:11.773
Vaya con Dios, man.

01:41:25.579 --> 01:41:30.166
This is unbelievable.
Twenty meters and closing.

01:41:30.292 --> 01:41:32.377
Fifteen.
How many?

01:41:32.461 --> 01:41:35.046
[ Hicks ]
Can't tell. Lots.

01:41:36.632 --> 01:41:39.884
"D" gun's down 50%..

01:41:39.969 --> 01:41:41.845
[Aliens Screeching ]

01:41:41.929 --> 01:41:45.056
"C" gun's right behind it.

01:41:47.018 --> 01:41:50.186
[ Hudson ]
Stopping them.
It ain't stopping them.

01:41:50.271 --> 01:41:55.275
- [ Hicks ] 150 rounds on "D."
- [ Hudson ]
Come on. Come on, baby.

01:41:55.359 --> 01:41:57.652
[ Hicks ]
Hundred rounds.

01:41:57.737 --> 01:42:00.405
[ Hudson ]
Come on! Come on!

01:42:00.489 --> 01:42:01.698
[ Beeping ]

01:42:05.411 --> 01:42:06.911
"D" gun's down to 20.

01:42:08.164 --> 01:42:10.582
Ten.

01:42:11.834 --> 01:42:13.251
Damn it!

01:42:14.879 --> 01:42:17.881
Wait! They're retreating.

01:42:23.137 --> 01:42:25.847
[ Ripley ]
The guns stopped them.

01:42:27.725 --> 01:42:29.684
You're right.

01:42:37.068 --> 01:42:38.985
Next time they walk
right up and knock.

01:42:39.070 --> 01:42:41.029
Yeah, but they don't
know that.

01:42:41.113 --> 01:42:43.865
They're probably looking
for other ways to get in.

01:42:44.909 --> 01:42:46.785
That'll take 'em a while.

01:42:46.911 --> 01:42:49.412
Maybe we got 'em
demoralized.
Shut up!

01:42:50.748 --> 01:42:53.208
I want you two
walking perimeter.

01:42:54.794 --> 01:42:57.378
Move!

01:43:03.594 --> 01:43:05.804
Hey, listen.

01:43:05.888 --> 01:43:08.807
We're all
in strung-out shape,

01:43:08.891 --> 01:43:12.185
but stay frosty
and alert.

01:43:13.604 --> 01:43:16.481
We can't afford to let
one of those bastards in here.

01:43:16.565 --> 01:43:18.733
All right.
Vmonos.

01:43:29.620 --> 01:43:31.621
How long's it been
since you got any sleep?

01:43:31.705 --> 01:43:35.333
Twenty-four hours?

01:43:35.417 --> 01:43:38.711
Hicks, I'm not
gonna end up
like those others.

01:43:38.796 --> 01:43:41.631
You'll take care
of it, won't you?

01:43:43.217 --> 01:43:47.762
If it comes to that,
I'll do us both.

01:43:49.473 --> 01:43:52.183
Listen, let's just make sure
it doesn't come to that.

01:43:52.309 --> 01:43:55.895
All right?
All right.

01:43:55.980 --> 01:44:01.192
Hey, I want to introduce you
to a personal friend of mine.

01:44:01.277 --> 01:44:05.196
This is an M-41A
pulse rifle, 10 millimeter,

01:44:05.281 --> 01:44:09.117
with an over-and-under
30 millimeter
pump-action grenade launcher.

01:44:09.201 --> 01:44:11.160
Feel the weight.

01:44:18.085 --> 01:44:20.378
Okay, what do I do?

01:44:25.801 --> 01:44:28.428
Okay, pull it in
tight here.
Right.

01:44:28.554 --> 01:44:30.847
Uh-huh.
Lean into it.
Mm-hmm.

01:44:30.931 --> 01:44:33.600
All right.
Now, it will kick some.

01:44:33.684 --> 01:44:37.228
All right.
When the counter
reads zero here, you-

01:44:37.354 --> 01:44:39.606
I press this up?
That's right.

01:44:41.692 --> 01:44:44.819
Get another one in quick.
Slap it in hard.

01:44:44.945 --> 01:44:47.947
Right.
And you're ready
to rock and roll.

01:44:48.073 --> 01:44:50.867
What's this?
That's the grenade
launcher.

01:44:50.951 --> 01:44:53.703
I don't think you
want to mess with that.

01:44:53.787 --> 01:44:57.790
You started this.
Show me everything.

01:44:57.875 --> 01:44:59.834
I can handle myself.

01:45:01.420 --> 01:45:03.379
Yeah, I noticed.

01:45:13.515 --> 01:45:15.475
How do you feel?

01:45:15.559 --> 01:45:19.062
All right, I guess.
One hell of a hangover.

01:45:20.606 --> 01:45:22.815
Look, Ripley,
I just want-
Forget it.

01:45:22.900 --> 01:45:24.859
Excuse me.

01:46:17.037 --> 01:46:19.789
[ Newt Groaning ]

01:46:19.873 --> 01:46:24.627
Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.
It's okay. It's okay.

01:47:35.365 --> 01:47:38.785
[ Whispering ]
Newt, wake up.

01:47:38.869 --> 01:47:40.787
Wha-
Be quiet.

01:47:40.871 --> 01:47:42.872
We're in trouble.

01:48:00.390 --> 01:48:02.183
- No!
- [ Screams ]

01:48:02.267 --> 01:48:04.936
Move, Newt!

01:48:19.952 --> 01:48:22.954
[ Both Grunting ]

01:48:25.415 --> 01:48:27.333
Hey!

01:48:27.417 --> 01:48:29.752
[ No Audio ]

01:48:36.343 --> 01:48:40.680
Help! Help!

01:48:40.764 --> 01:48:42.723
Hicks!
Somebody!

01:48:42.808 --> 01:48:44.725
[ Hicks ]
Say again, Bishop.

01:48:44.810 --> 01:48:48.146
You've got it
into auto-refuel mode,
and it's sequencing right?

01:48:48.272 --> 01:48:51.274
[ Bishop On Radio ]
That's right.
Okay, good. Stay on it.

01:48:51.400 --> 01:48:54.944
[ Indistinct ]
Get back to me when you've
activated the launch cycle.

01:48:55.028 --> 01:48:58.281
Roger.
He's at the uplink tower.

01:48:58.407 --> 01:49:00.908
Good.
Terrific.

01:49:02.619 --> 01:49:05.621
[ Ripley ]
Hicks! Hicks! Hicks!
[ Newt ] Help!

01:49:05.706 --> 01:49:08.291
- Help! Help!
- Hicks, help us!

01:49:08.375 --> 01:49:12.461
- Break the glass!
Break it. Break it.
- Yes.

01:49:12.546 --> 01:49:14.547
I'll try.

01:49:28.312 --> 01:49:29.979
[ Scurrying ]

01:49:31.690 --> 01:49:34.734
[ Clinking ]

01:49:34.818 --> 01:49:37.278
Ripley, I'm scared.

01:49:37.362 --> 01:49:39.363
Me too.

01:49:44.828 --> 01:49:46.829
Stay here.

01:49:55.547 --> 01:49:58.549
[Alarm Blaring ]

01:49:58.634 --> 01:50:01.677
It's the medlab. Hudson!

01:50:01.762 --> 01:50:05.097
Vasquez, meet me in medlab.
We got a fire.

01:50:05.182 --> 01:50:07.183
[ Hudson On Radio ]
We're on our way.

01:50:10.062 --> 01:50:12.063
They're coming, Newt.

01:50:17.402 --> 01:50:19.528
[ Screaming ]

01:50:19.613 --> 01:50:21.781
- [ Grunts ]
- [ Screaming Continues ]

01:50:21.865 --> 01:50:23.407
[ Grunts ]

01:50:26.662 --> 01:50:28.871
[ Screaming ]

01:50:32.542 --> 01:50:34.210
[ Gasping ]

01:50:35.629 --> 01:50:38.839
[ Screaming Continues ]

01:50:44.638 --> 01:50:46.722
Shoot it out!

01:50:50.727 --> 01:50:52.603
- Hudson!
- Jesus.

01:50:54.564 --> 01:50:56.107
[ Gasping ]

01:50:56.191 --> 01:50:58.526
Christ, kid, look out!

01:51:06.451 --> 01:51:07.451
Fucking die.

01:51:19.339 --> 01:51:22.550
Over there! Ready?
Yeah! Yeah!

01:51:22.634 --> 01:51:24.260
[ Hicks ]
Now!

01:51:27.764 --> 01:51:29.640
Hudson?
Yeah. All clear.

01:51:29.766 --> 01:51:32.310
Nailed the other one.
lt's history, man.
[ Coughing ]

01:51:33.729 --> 01:51:35.646
Jesus.

01:51:36.815 --> 01:51:40.401
Burke-
[ Coughs ]
It was Burke.

01:51:42.654 --> 01:51:45.865
I say we grease this rat-fuck
son of a bitch right now.

01:51:45.949 --> 01:51:48.868
Just doesn't make
any goddamn sense.

01:51:51.830 --> 01:51:55.875
He figured that
he could get an alien
back through quarantine...

01:51:55.959 --> 01:51:58.669
if one of us
was impregnated-

01:51:59.963 --> 01:52:02.173
whatever you call it-

01:52:02.257 --> 01:52:04.842
and then frozen
for the trip home.

01:52:04.926 --> 01:52:08.971
Nobody would know
about the embryos
we were carrying-

01:52:09.056 --> 01:52:11.098
me and Newt.

01:52:12.934 --> 01:52:14.894
Wait a minute, now.
We'd all know.

01:52:14.978 --> 01:52:17.229
Yes. The only way
he could do it...

01:52:17.314 --> 01:52:21.067
is if he sabotaged certain
freezers on the way home.

01:52:21.151 --> 01:52:23.736
Namely yours.

01:52:23.820 --> 01:52:27.698
Then he could
jettison the bodies
and make up any story he liked.

01:52:27.783 --> 01:52:33.162
Fuck! He's dead.
You're dog meat, pal.

01:52:34.164 --> 01:52:36.082
This is so nuts.

01:52:36.166 --> 01:52:38.793
I mean, listen-
Listen to what you're saying.

01:52:38.877 --> 01:52:41.545
It's paranoid delusion.

01:52:41.630 --> 01:52:45.966
It's really sad.
It's pathetic.

01:52:46.051 --> 01:52:49.845
You know, Burke, I don't know
which species is worse.

01:52:49.930 --> 01:52:53.224
You don't see them
fucking each other over
for a goddamn percentage.

01:52:53.308 --> 01:52:56.435
All right.
We waste him. No offense.

01:52:56.520 --> 01:52:58.187
No! He's gotta go back-

01:53:00.357 --> 01:53:02.983
They cut the power.
What do you mean,
they cut the power?

01:53:03.068 --> 01:53:04.652
How could they cut the power, man?
They're animals.

01:53:04.736 --> 01:53:07.321
I want you two with trackers,
checking the corridors! Move!

01:53:07.406 --> 01:53:09.323
[ Ripley ]
Gorman, watch Burke!
I got him.

01:53:09.408 --> 01:53:11.700
Newt, stay close.

01:53:15.205 --> 01:53:18.290
I'll go this side.
You do that, man.

01:53:19.292 --> 01:53:22.294
[ Tracker Clicking ]

01:53:42.023 --> 01:53:44.817
Anything?
[ Hudson ]
There's something.

01:53:44.901 --> 01:53:48.112
[ Beeping ]
It's inside the complex.

01:53:48.196 --> 01:53:50.197
You're just reading me.

01:53:51.158 --> 01:53:53.075
No, no, it ain't you.

01:53:55.245 --> 01:53:58.914
They're inside-
inside the perimeter.
They're in here.

01:53:58.999 --> 01:54:02.460
[ Ripley ]
Hudson, stay cool!
Vasquez?

01:54:02.544 --> 01:54:04.587
[ Clicking ]

01:54:05.755 --> 01:54:09.133
[ Beeping ]

01:54:09.217 --> 01:54:10.801
Hudson may be right.

01:54:10.927 --> 01:54:14.054
Get back, both of you!
[ Hudson ]
The signal's weird.

01:54:15.432 --> 01:54:18.100
Must be some interference
or something.

01:54:18.185 --> 01:54:20.102
There's movement
all over the place!

01:54:20.187 --> 01:54:23.522
Get back to Operations.
It's game time.

01:54:23.607 --> 01:54:25.983
Newt.

01:54:27.527 --> 01:54:30.404
Seal the door.
Hurry!

01:54:30.489 --> 01:54:33.949
Come on! Come on!
Come on! Get back!

01:54:34.034 --> 01:54:35.951
Work fast.

01:54:39.331 --> 01:54:42.500
Cover your eyes, Newt.
Don't look at the light.

01:54:42.584 --> 01:54:45.586
Movement. Signal's clean.

01:54:45.670 --> 01:54:47.588
Range, 20 meters.

01:54:47.672 --> 01:54:49.840
They found a way in,
something we missed.

01:54:49.925 --> 01:54:51.842
We didn't miss anything.

01:54:51.927 --> 01:54:55.721
Eighteen.
Seventeen meters.

01:54:55.805 --> 01:54:58.182
Something under the floor,
not in the plans.
I don't know.

01:54:58.266 --> 01:55:00.351
- Fifteen meters.
- Ripley!

01:55:00.435 --> 01:55:03.938
- Definitely inside
the barricades.
- Let's go.

01:55:05.565 --> 01:55:07.441
Thirteen meters.
That's right
outside the door.

01:55:07.567 --> 01:55:10.194
Hicks, Vasquez, get back!
This is a big fucking signal.

01:55:10.278 --> 01:55:13.489
- How you doing, Vasquez?
Talk to me.
- Almost there.

01:55:15.116 --> 01:55:17.493
That's it.

01:55:17.577 --> 01:55:21.872
Twelve meters. Eleven.
[ High-pitched Beeping ]

01:55:21.957 --> 01:55:24.458
- Ten.
- Then they're right on us.

01:55:24.543 --> 01:55:27.795
- Nine meters.
- Remember- short,
controlled bursts.

01:55:27.879 --> 01:55:29.213
Eight meters.

01:55:32.217 --> 01:55:34.885
Seven.

01:55:34.970 --> 01:55:37.888
- Six.
- It can't be.
That's inside the room.

01:55:37.973 --> 01:55:41.016
- It's reading right, man. Look!
- Well, you're not reading
it right.

01:55:43.603 --> 01:55:48.190
[ Hudson ]
Five meters, man.
Four. What the hell?

01:55:48.275 --> 01:55:50.734
[ Beeping Continues ]

01:55:50.860 --> 01:55:54.446
Oh, my God.
Oh, sh-
Give me the light.

01:56:08.587 --> 01:56:10.588
[ Shouting ]

